{
  "page_number": 4,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Preface"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Target group of this manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "4"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Preface"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This manual is intended for agrarians and others trained in working in the field of agriculture, people that are competent to operate these machine, as required by national legislation, and who have knowledge of assembly activities."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "For your safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Ensure that you are familiar with the contents of this manual before you start using or assembling the implement. This will ensure that you obtain an optimum result and are working safely."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSafety requirements\u00ab on page 10."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Should you have any questions or if anything is unclear, please contact the manufacturer."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Make sure that this manual is available to all persons who will be working with this machine. In this way, you will:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 avoid accidents,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 respect the warranty conditions,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 always have a good functioning machine in perfect working order."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "For the employer"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 All personnel who operate this machine must be authorised to do so in terms of the applicable national legislation."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7  All personnel are to be trained in the use of the machine regularly (at least once a year) in accordance with employers' liability insurance association guidelines. Untrained or unauthorised individuals are not permitted to use the machinery."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 You are responsible for the safe operation and maintenance of your machine. You must ensure that you and anyone else who is going to operate, maintain or work around the unit be familiar with the operating and maintenance procedures and related safety information as mentioned in this manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 You are responsible for providing personal protective gear to personnel who use the machine or who are performing maintenance or repairs on it. This includes: safety goggles, safety shoes, safety gloves, etc."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 5,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Meaning of symbols"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Preface"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Various symbols are used to provide a clear understanding of the text.. These are explained below:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 A dot is placed before lists."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 A triangle marks tasks you have to perform."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae An arrow refers to a different place in the text."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In addition, we use pictograms to help you easily find certain text sections."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION The words 'Tip' and 'Hint' are followed by tips or hints for operation."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The warning triangle indicates important safety instructions. Failing to comply with these may result in:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 serious operating malfunctions of the machine;"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 damage to the machine;"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 injuries or accidents."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spanner indicates tips for assembly or adjustment work."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A star indicates that examples will follow that are intended to clarify the text."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "All directional rotations are to be interpreted when facing in direction of travel."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "5"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 6,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "For your safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Other guidelines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "6"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In this chapter you will find general safety instructions. In every next chapter you will find more specific safety instructions not described here."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not risk injury or death by ignoring good safety instructions."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Many risks can happen when working with agricultural machines. Avoid accidents! Do not take risks! Be alert! Think safety! Work in safety!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Disregard of the 'Safety instructions', inadequate maintenance, use of the machine other than for its intended purpose, overloading or unauthorised modification of the machine, renders the manufacturer's warranty and responsibility void."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Familiarise yourself with the function of all machine controls and the safety instructions, prior to any usage of the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Incorrect use of the machine may lead to dangerous situations. For this reason, you should always work carefully and never under high time pressure."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Comply with the rules"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In addition to the instructions above you should comply with the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 measures to prevent accidents,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 general safety instructions, occupational health requirements and road traffic regulations,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 instructions in this manual,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Rules regarding use, maintenance and repairs."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 7,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Warning stickers"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Various warning stickers have been affixed to the machine for safety reasons. Do not remove them! Always follow the instructions supplied and be alert to possible dangers."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always keep the safety stickers and symbols clean and clearly legible. Replace safety decals that are missing, damaged or have become illegible. If original parts on which a safety decal or sign was installed are replaced, be sure that the replacement part also displays the current decal or sign."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "7"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 8,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Explanation for warning stickers"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "8"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Stop the engine and remove the keys from the ignition"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Switch the engine off as soon as you leave the tractor. Remove the key from the ignition to prevent the tractor from being started unintentionally while you are in the danger zone. This especially applies when changing the settings or while maintenance and repairs are carried out."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Keep clear from a running machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser is spread over a great distance during operation. Ensure that nobody comes within working reach of the machine during operation. Do not come into the working area before all parts of the machine are standing still."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The power lift must only be operated outside of the danger zone"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the area between the tractor and the machine, there is a danger of being pinned down by the power lift. The power lift must therefore only be engaged from beyond the danger zone. Secure the tractor with the parking brake and wheel chocks to ensure it would not roll away."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not approach the machine until it has come to a complete standstill"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The rotating parts of the machine never come to an immediate halt, they always wind down. The moving parts of a machine are not always visible. Do not approach the machine until all moving parts have come to a complete halt."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never go underneath an elevated, unsecured machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine or parts of the machine could accidentally fall due to waning pressure, for instance. Always place the machine on proper supports if you have to work under the machine!"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 9,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only lift the machine at the lifting points"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If a machine is being elevated, only attach it to the indicated lifting points. Never go underneath an elevated machine. Allow for any possible movements of the elevated machine, whether wanted or not."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful of getting jammed or pinched"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the machine is engaged or operated unintentionally you could get struck in moving parts, which could lead to injury. Be extra alert when working in the vicinity of moving parts. Always keep in mind that the motor or parts of the machine could still be retaining some energy."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Read the user's manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The instruction manual contains procedures for working correctly to ensure safe work, as well as dangers one could possibly encounter. Keep to these procedures as described and give due consideration to the safety measures in place!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not exceed the maximum hydraulic pressure of 210 bars"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Prevent the pressure in the hydraulic system from exceeding 210 bars! Working with higher pressure may damage your machine and result in dangerous situations."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Motor vehicles with limited speed (<40 km/h), agricultural and forestry tractors and their trailers, as well as other vehicles, must be provided with an orange triangle with a red reflector at the rear in the form of a truncated triangle."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "9"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 10,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Safety requirements"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Intended use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "10"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This part contains all the requirements, everything that is not permitted and requirements for each form of usage, maintenance and reparation of the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The chapters in the manual contain additional safety measures."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Knowledge of the safety regulations forms the basis for safety and proper usage of the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always follow the safety instructions. most accidents are avoidable. Do not run the risk of serious or fatal accidents through ignorance of these safety instructions."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This machine is exclusively intended to spread granular products, specifically fertiliser types and seeds."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Any other application would be considered to be irregular. The manufacturer is not responsible for damage that may result from such usage; risks are taken exclusively by the user."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The instructions, maintenance requirements and reparation stipulations as indicated by the manufacturer must be adhered to at all times."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Responsibility of the user"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The user may only operate the machine if he/she:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is familiar with the basic safety requirements and the working conditions requirements,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is familiar with current traffic regulations,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 has been duly instructed on how to work on/with the machine and the related dangers,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 has read and understood this manual,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is familiar with all the systems and operating elements and their functions,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is familiar with the requirements for using, maintaining and repairing machines."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It will be too late for that once you are working!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Irresponsible usage could lead to injury to the user or third parties and could lead to damage to the machine."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 11,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Authorisation"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Clothes/protection"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only to be used by an authorised person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine may be used by authorised people only. A person is authorised if he/she:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 received training as required by the national authorities,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 has taken responsibility as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbPerson\u00ab on page 10."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Maintenance and repairs by experts"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance, replacement of parts and repairs to the machine may only be performed by experts."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A person is considered to be an expert if he/she has sufficient knowledge in the fields of safety, maintenance, production and repairs as a result of training and experience."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance or repairs performed by an unskilled person could lead to injury and damage the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Wear close-fitting clothing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Avoid wearing loose fitting clothing. Loose clothing could become entangled with moving parts, which could lead to serious consequences."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Ensure personal protection"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Ensure your personal protection. Outfit:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 safety goggles,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 safety shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 safety gloves."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Prevent hearing damage"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Your hearing could be damaged when working with the tractor and machine with noise levels in excess of 80 dB. Use the appropriate ear protection in order to prevent hearing damage. Remaining in an area with high noise levels for a long period of time could lead to serious damage to your hearing."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "What to do in the event of injury"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the event of injury and if you suspect that you made contact with materials you should:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 clean the point of contact with a lot of water,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 contact your physician immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "11"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 12,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Workplace"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "12"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be used and operated by 1 person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine may only be operated by one person, from the tractor. Operating the machine from the tractor will keep you out of harm's way. Other people should not be in the immediate vicinity of the machine and the tractor. Those who are within the working area and the danger zone could be injured."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity and keep a constant eye on it at the start, as well as while you are working with the machine. Familiarise yourself with the immediate vicinity. Do not start working until all people and obstacles within the working area and danger zone of the tractor and machine have been removed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never stay or allow anyone to stay within the danger area while the machine is running! If there are people within the working area and the danger zone it could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work with a closed cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser dust can blow indoors through open windows, doors or other openings. Moreover, the sound level is higher in an open cabin. It is therefore recommended to always work with a closed cabin with active carbon filters in the air inlets. Fertiliser dust and a high sound level can cause physical damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the state of the tractor and machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only work with the tractor and machine if they are in good condition Always check that:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 all lighting, safety and warning provisions must be mounted correctly and be in good working condition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the lifting and pulling capabilities must be sufficient,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see paragraph \u00bbCalculate the axle load with tractor-mounted machines\u00ab on page 13,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the tractor must be suitable for the machine, such as in the area of stability, engine capability, axle load and total weight,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 it is sufficient for the working with the machine and for transport."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Adhere to maximum permissible axle loads, total weights and transport dimensions! Using a tractor which is not proper can cause serious or deadly injuries or machine damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the tractor's technical details."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 13,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Calculate the axle load with tractor-mounted machines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Put a fire extinguisher in place"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Carry a fire extinguisher at all times, especially when operating in dry crop materials. This should be a multi-purpose ABC rated extinguisher with a 5 kg capacity, approved by the appropriate authority. Mount this on the tractor and/or on the machine. Fire could damage the machine and cause injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use active carbon filters"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Harmful gasses and mists could enter the air duct of the tractor while it is in use. An active carbon filter should therefore be mounted in the air ventilation of the tractor. Harmful materials could cause serious personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Ensure the tractor is safe when leaving it"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never leave the tractor without:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the PTO shaft,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the tractor engine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the key must be removed from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Leaving the tractor unsafe could create dangerous situations that could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Responding to problems"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the event of operational problems you should:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 stop immediately,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor and machine off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 attend to the problem or call in the assistance of an expert."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never use the tractor in a closed area"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The tractor must never be used in a closed area. Exhaust fumes collect without being noticed. Exhaust fumes can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The following is of importance with the loading machine to ensure safe operation:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the maximum load of the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the maximum axle load of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 weight distribution over the axles,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 and the carry load per wheel."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "At least 20% own weight from the tractor must rest on the front axle and 45% on the rear axle in order to maintain good manoeuvrability. Check if these conditions are adhered to before purchasing a machine! Adhere to maximum permissible axle loads, total weights and transport dimensions! Using a tractor which is not proper can cause serious or deadly injuries or tractor and machine damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "13"
    }
  ]
}

