{
  "page_number": 17,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety decals"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the condition of the machine before use"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the following before using the machine:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is the machine in a proper, functioning condition?"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 are all lights, safety and warning provisions correctly mounted and in good working condition?"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 are the brakes of the machine working properly and have they been adjusted to the correct position?"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using an unsafe machine could result in personal injury and damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The machine should only carry, not pull!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is not permitted to use the machine for pulling as this would have detrimental consequences to its construction. This could lead to dangerous situations for bystanders, unsafe operation or damage to crops."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not stand on the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Being on the machine during activities and transport is prohibited. You may only be on the parts of the machine intended for the purpose if it is standing still and prevented from rolling by means of parking brake and wheel chocks. Being on the machine while in any other state could lead to serious injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never work on a running machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never work on the machine while it is running. A running machine has several moving parts which can not be seen. Wait until all parts have come to a complete halt. Moving parts can cause serious injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Follow the instructions on the stickers"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The safety decals on the machine give important advice for a risk free operation. Respect them to ensure your safety."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Replace any safety decals and safety signs missing or illegible"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When parts with a safety or warning decal are replaced, the replacement part must be provided with the same safety or warning decal. Stickers that are not legible must be replaced so that they would be clearly legible at all times."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "17"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 18,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Hydraulic system"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Electronic control system"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "18"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use the correct coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only use coupling shafts complying with the manufacturer's specification for that specific use! In order to ensure protection of both man and machine exercise extreme caution when working at a coupling shaft other then described in this manual and/or on the instruction at the coupling shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Modifications to and other special activities at coupling shafts are only permitted with the explicit written instruction and approval of the manufacturers of both the machine and the coupling shaft! Use the correct tools and original parts to ensure a good performance and maximum safety. The use of an incorrect coupling shaft can cause damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Mount the appropriate protection"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Externally accessible coupling shafts, the tractor's PTO shafts and machine input-axle must be equipped with appropriate guards and tubes. Working without guarding can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Replace protective coupling shaft tubes when required"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Replace the coupling shaft protection sleeves at the first signs of wear. Protection sleeves can wear without being noticed. Worn or damaged protection sleeves can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protect the PTO shaft end well"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Slide the protection sleeve over the PTO shaft as soon as the coupling shaft has been removed. Clothing could become entangled into an unprotected PTO shaft end that could lead to serious injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Hydraulic oil is under high pressure"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never try to stop a leak with your fingers. Never try to locate a hydraulic leak or try to contain it by hand! When inspecting always use appropriate aid (e.g. a piece of wood or sheet metal) and wear safety goggles, safety gloves and gloves! High pressure fluid easily penetrates skin and clothes, causing severe injuries. In the event of injury, contact your physician immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Disconnect the control box"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Disconnect the control box from the electric system as soon as no more functions are needed in order to prevent unintentional operation. Keeping the control box connect can be dangerous and can damage the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "as well as cause bodily injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Battery cables must be connected properly"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always disconnect the battery cable (negative pole) from the electric system when working on the machine. Connect the battery cables correctly: Positive pole first, followed by the negative pole. Always equip the positive pole with the appropriate protective cap to avoid a short circuit as this could lead to damage to the tractor and machine."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 19,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only use after training"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine may not be operated before the user has been properly instructed by the dealer or an authorised representative of the manufacturer."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Ensure that you are familiar with all systems and control machines and their functions prior to working with them! It will be too late for that once you are working! Careless usage could lead to injury and damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be used and operated by 1 person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine may only be operated by one person, from the tractor. Operating the machine from the tractor will keep you out of harm's way. Other people should not be in the immediate vicinity of the machine and the tractor. Those who are within the working area and the danger zone could be injured."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity and keep a constant eye on it at the start, as well as while you are working with the machine. Familiarise yourself with the immediate vicinity. Do not start working until all people and obstacles within the working area and danger zone of the tractor and machine have been removed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never stay or allow anyone to stay within the danger area while the machine is running! If there are people within the working area and the danger zone it could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not stand on the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Being on the machine during activities and transport is prohibited. You may only be on the parts of the machine intended for the purpose if it is standing still and prevented from rolling. Being on the machine while in any other state could lead to serious injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Keep the protection intact"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The protection of the machine, e.g. shields and guards, protects from penetrating into danger areas! Therefore all protection must be kept in optimal condition and moved into the right position prior to starting to work! The absence of protective gear could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "19"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 20,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Transport"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "On the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "20"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the decoupling ropes of the quick coupling"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The decoupling ropes must never be tense and must provide sufficient freedom for movement, even with the power lift in the lowest position as it could otherwise accidentally disconnect the quick coupling."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Drive carefully"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Moving behaviour, manoeuvrability and braking performance are influenced by a trailed machine. When taking turns, pay attention to the extended width/length (turning circle) and/or large mass (sluggishness) of the machine. Ensure sufficient braking effect and safe manageability! Careless driving could lead to serious injury and damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Adjust the driving speed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "High driving speeds and uneven surfaces on the road or field can put considerable strain on the machine and cause the tractor or machine to be overstrained, which could lead to damage. Always adjust the driving speed to the conditions of the environment and the terrain! When driving up and down hills and across slopes, do not make any sudden turns!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not leave the driving cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never leave the operator's seat during operation or transport. The driver can be in the danger zone of the tractor or the machine and could not have a proper view of the immediate vicinity. This could lead to injury to the driver or third parties."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not allow the machine to tilt"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When driving up and down hills and across slopes, do not make any sudden turns! Do not drive transverse on a slope with a steep angle. Tilting can cause serious machine damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Blockade of a security device"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In case of blockade or operation of a security device, never work on the machine without:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the PTO shaft,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the tractor engine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the key must be removed from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "PTO shaft rotates after disengaging"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "After switching off the PTO shaft, the machine will continue running because of inertia. Keep a safe distance to the machine until the moving parts have come to a complete stop. Approaching the machine while it is rotating can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 21,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Always keep to the prescribed maintenance intervals"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Take the machine for inspection and maintenance at the intervals as prescribed in this manual. All of the manufacturer's responsibility and the guarantee will become null and void if the prescribed intervals are not adhered to."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Performed by an authorised person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always have an authorised expert perform maintenance and repairs as prescribed in, as prescribed in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbAuthorisation\u00ab on page 11."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance performed in an inexpert manner could lead to unsafe work situations or damage to the machine or crops."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never use the tractor in a closed area"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The tractor must never be used in a closed area. Exhaust fumes collect without being noticed. Exhaust fumes can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protect the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser and other salts have a great influence on the rate of corrosion. Empty the hopper at the end of activities. Protect the machine by always cleaning it after using such material and patch breaks in the paint. Corrosion affects the strength of the construction and the operation of the machine, which could lead to a shortened lifespan."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only use original parts when replacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using other non-genuine parts could lead to problems and unsafe situations when using the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can use the supplied parts manual (either as a printout or as a PDF in the included memory card) to locate the correct part number."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never work on the machine while it is running"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never work on the machine while it is running. A running machine has several moving parts which can not be seen. These can cause serious injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not change the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not modify the machine in any way. Unauthorised modifications may impair the function and/or safety and affect the life of the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "21"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 22,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Safety"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "22"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with materials"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You should only come into contact with the materials when cleaning the machine. Always wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves, shoes and goggles. Read and adhere to the additional safety instructions and the of the material producer. Contact with the materials could lead to injury. Contact your physician in such an event!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Explosion danger because of nitrate"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertilisers hat contain nitrate can create an explosion danger if they come into contact with fire. All fertiliser remnants should therefore be removed from voids, corners, tubes and tubing before welding, cutting or grinding on the machine. Explosions could cause damage to the machine and lead to personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Prevent unintentional operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Render all parts that could contain residual energy safe, as well as all parts that conduct energy such as compressed air, hydraulics and electricity. Release all pressure from the system and disconnect the pipes and cables. Unintended operation could lead to injury."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 23,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Applications of the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This PTO shaft driven machine is suited for spreading granular fertiliser on the field and grazing land. It is attached"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connection to a gusset in the headland"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Connection to a gusset in the headland"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Software"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Software"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "CentreFlow spreading system"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 to the three-point power lift of the tractor (Cat. II),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 with linkage frame (optional extras) for tractors with power lift of Cat. III, or"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 to the trailer supplied for this purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Border spreading is possible by using the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Hydraulic border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the ExactLine border spreading system."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "GEOSPREAD with GEOCONTROL"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With the GEOCONTROL software, connection of"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the passes on the headland,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sloping passes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 and last incomplete pass improved."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Gored spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Even a headland connecting at a slant (angle) is correctly connected in the pass by the variable width distribution of the GEOSPREAD."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This manual contains a description for the GEOSPREAD control system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This manual contains a description for the GEOSPREAD control system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae For a detailed description see the instruction manual of the software."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This rotary type spreader has two spreading discs. Each has eight by a dosing plate on top of the spreading disc. Both of the dosing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "vanes. They are mounted level so that the fertiliser is spread over the land in a constant horizontal flow. The spreading quantity is regulated plates are located right on top of the discharge bushings. The fertiliser falls on the turning spreading disc. The discharge point is determined by the opening in the discharge bushing behind the vanes. This means that the fertiliser granules are already turning before they come into contact with the vanes on the spreading disc. This prevents granules from breaking apart and becoming powdery. The agitator mounted below in the hopper provides for a constant stream of fertiliser dust, seeds or granules to the dosing opening(s). Moreover, the agitator prevents the chunks of fertiliser from blocking"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "one or more dosing openings."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "23"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 24,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Adjust carefully"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Application rate"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Fine dosing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fine application handle Normal dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Fine application handle Normal dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fine application handle Fine application setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Fine application handle Fine application setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "24"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreader has two actuators per dosing unit to set the application rate and working width independently of each other. Moreover, it is possible to shut 2 of the 3 dosing openings so that the application rate can also be set precisely with a low flowrate, while the risk of blockages remains limited."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine is equipped with two actuators, which service a dosing plate each, in order to set the application rate. This actuator can open the dosing plate in every required position. In this way, accurate dosing independent of the driving speed is possible. It is also possible to control the dosing setting with external sensors, for example, a nitrogen sensor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbApplication rate\u00ab on page 66."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The actuators are controlled by means of the spreader software. By means of weight sensors, the spreader continuously measures the discharge volumes and corrects it as needed with the application rate. If you want to close on one side, you can choose the function on the control box, after which one of the two dosing plates will be closed immediately."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Normal dosing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "For precise dosing over a wide range of settings, a spreader with 3 openings is applied per disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Fine application"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreader is equipped with a fine spreader as standard equipment to spread low application rates. This fine spreader can be adjusted with a lever per dosing unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Low application rates require a small dosing opening. In order"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 to finely adjust the settings"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 and to counter the blockage"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "a transition to the opening, which is open wider, is desirable."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "2 of the 3 dosing openings are closed when using the fine dosing setting."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The fertiliser now flows through one opening that is opened wider, giving an accurate, reliable flow, also at low application rate."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 25,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Width distribution with GEOSPREAD"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Actuator for discharge point adjustment"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Actuator for discharge point adjustment"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Combined control with GEOSPREAD system"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Discharge point letter setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The spreading pattern is determined by the transverse distribution."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The discharge point is the place where the fertiliser granules come into touch with the vanes of the spreading disc and substantially determines width distribution."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Actuators for setting the discharge point"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The GEOSPREAD execution has two additional actuators which set the discharge point. The discharge point setting depends on the fertiliser type and the flowrate in kg/min."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The letter setting for the discharge point for the working width and application rate is given in the spreading chart. The spreading computer determines the correct setting with the input working and spreading chart data."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading pattern form"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading pattern is normally a triangle that completely overlaps. A trapezoidal spreading pattern may result, depending on the type of fertiliser, working width and application rate. This spreading pattern has an overlapping area of less than 100%."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Reducing working width during the pass"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control of discharge point and dosing via the 4 actuators enables the calculation of a variable working width. By means of this, the working width can be varied at an angle on the headlands (gored spreading) or an incomplete final pass without interrupting the spreading for this purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spray computer can determine the time of full or partial closure with the GPS and the data of the sprayed passes. This takes place on the headland and during gored spreading. The quantity of over or under fertilisation is substantially reduced by this."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "25"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 26,
