    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Active sections"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Active sections"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The active sections are displayed in black triangles in the main screen for both sides:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 The working width of 24 metres is divided into sections and controlled by the GEOCONTROL."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The working width reduction per section is displayed in the main screen by leaving out a part of the triangle at a time and displaying the new working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Here, sections to the left are closed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The GEOCONTROL screen also displays the section of activities in a bar below the screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the accuracy of the discharge point letter setting by conducting a spreading pattern test (tray test)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSpreading pattern check (tray test)\u00ab on page 76."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Take note of the exact driving distance and make sure there are tramlines."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you want to change the application rate or change to another fertiliser type (with similar working width and driving speed), you only have to enter a new flowrate starting value and relevant dosing setting and adapt the discharge point letter setting, if required."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "26"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 27,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "RATE control"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "MULTIRATE"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Greenseeker"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "RATE control is a variable application rate triggered by an external signal."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "No additional licence key is required."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the GEOCONTROL instruction manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "MULTIRATE can be used on your ISOBUS weighing spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "An additional licence key is required to enable the software module."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "MULTIRATE automatically adjusts the amount of fertiliser per side. The application rate to the left and right is independently based on a rate map."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can do this on the basis of a maximum of 8 measuring points of the rate map."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is a combined functionality between the spreader and the terminal, providing the option of using two or more variable quantities in the working width of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A total of 8 VRA sections are supported by the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To achieve full functionality with the IsoMatch PRO Terminal, you also need the IsoMatch GEOCONTROL licence key."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When MULTIRATE signals are received, the following icon is visible."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the GEOCONTROL instruction manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The ISOBUS supports the Farmfacts Greeseeker sensor. From Greenseeker version 06.00.00.0257 onwards, the software supports the reception of the external signal. Section control continues working through the Task Controller."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "27"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 28,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading pattern"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Full field spreading pattern"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Optimum distribution of the fertiliser with minimum impact on the environment can be achieved through the settings and tools described."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The full field spreading pattern overlaps 100%"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A triangular spreading pattern that completely overlaps can be expected with most fertiliser types with an average working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Influence of the GEOSPREAD function"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "One-sided boundary spreading with border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can drive along the field edge with a half spreading pattern filled to 100% with the border spreading plate and one closed dosing unit. You have to optimise the spreading pattern and thereby overcome environmental pollution when adjusting the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With the hydraulic border spreading plate, one-sided boundary spreading is also possible at the left."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "28"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A trapezium-shaped spreading pattern will gradually be converted to a triangular spreading pattern with complete overlap by reducing the working width on sloping passes."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 29,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Boundary track spreading with ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is possible to spread right up to the border (boundary track spreading) from the first sprayer tramline with ExactLine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A ExactLine is available for the right and the left."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Selecting the pattern for border spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is not possible to completely cover the field border at the application rate and not have anything go beyond the border. Current environmental standards only allow for minimal loss over the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "ExactLine bends the fertiliser granules in such a way that loss over the edge of the border is restricted to the bare minimum and it provides as full a spreading pattern as possible."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "ExactLine has 'environment' and 'yield' settings for precisely adjusting border spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "29"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 30,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The ISO control system"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The automatic weighing system"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The ISO control system uses the ISOBUS communication protocol, which makes it suitable for tractors that are also equipped with an ISOBUS communication system. For tractors that still do not have an ISOBUS connection, your dealer can supply the universal IsoMatch terminal to which you can connect all ISOBUS machines."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreader uses weighcells to continuously measure the quantity of fertiliser that is being spread. The computer in the distribution box compares these values with the set application rate and corrects as needed by further opening or closing the dosing unit. The tractor's electronics or an extra (gps) sensor measures the current required driving speed and localisation."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The working width and the start/stop time is controlled with field boundaries and headlands. Field data imported from a new management system or a newly created field boundary is used for this purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "30"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 31,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "flowrate (kg/min)"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Getting familiar with the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The computer calculates the required fertiliser flowrate with the following formula:"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Flowrate required = (kg/min)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Working width (m) x Driving speed (km/h) x Application rate (kg/ha)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "600"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Automatic Calibration test"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With the data from the spreading chart book and the automatic calibration tests that the spreader carries out every 75 kg or every minute, the computer determines what dosing setting corresponds with what flowrate. This relation is different for each fertiliser type, after all. A shorter interim time can be set for shorter fields."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use spreading chart"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To determine the relation between dosing setting and flowrate, the computer needs at least 1 measuring point. This value comes from the spreading chart. By means of the automatic calibration tests, the computer repeatedly corrects the relation between flowrate and dosing setting. In this way, the relation is always current and the spreader reacts in the right way to changes, for example, in driving speed or in cases of over and under dosing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To prevent field conditions such as slopes and holes or steering, braking actions and vibrations from influencing the measured values, the machine is equipped with a reference sensor. By means of the reference sensor signal, the spreader corrects the influence of the factors mentioned."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "If the hopper content becomes less than 100 kg, the control system switches off the automatic calibration. Measurement accuracy declines in such a way that new automatic calibration cannot produce a better discharge curve."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "31"
    }
  ]
}

