{
  "page_number": 38,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Inspection of the supplied machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Mounting instructions"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "38"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The machine would generally be assembled and delivered ready-foruse by the dealer. The dealer is also responsible for providing instructions for use and maintenance. He/she must also ensure that the required documents are provided, such as:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 manual,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 spare parts manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 spreading chart book,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 testing and approval documents where required."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If parts are missing or have been damaged during transport, you should report that to your dealer directly on delivery."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before the machine can be used, various parts and supplied accessories must be unpacked and assembled."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "TIP In addition to the assembly instructions, use the parts book to locate the parts and their positions on the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use sturdy hoisting equipment"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use the hoisting points on the machine to hook up your approved slings or hoisting chains. If the machine is hoisted incorrectly or with inferior equipment it could fall from the sling, resulting in material damage and possible physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work on a clean surface"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before you start mounting, you should clean the surface and the directly surrounding area where you place the machine. A machine that is placed on pieces of packaging or parts, may slide away during mounting with material damage and possibly physical injury as a result."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Accessories and parts must be correctly mounted"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Assemble accessories and parts according to specifications and attach them only for their designated purpose; ensure that it is locked correctly. Accessories and parts which are not fastened securely could lead to personal injury and damage to the crop and machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Tighten all bolts and nuts"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check that all the nuts and bolts are well set. Check this again after one hour of use"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after delivery and"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after maintenance or repairs have been carried out."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never check holes to be lined up by inserting your fingers"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use a pin. Movement of the machine or parts may cause severe physical injury."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 39,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Control box"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while mounting the spreader. Work carefully:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 place the machine on adequate supports,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the PTO shaft,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Switch off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In addition to these assembly instructions, use the parts book to locate the parts and their positions on the machine or the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you use the IsoMatch or another loose-standing control box to operate the spreader, you must first assemble the support."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The fixing materials and the assembly instructions are delivered with the control box. Additionally, you will find brief assembly instructions below."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you use the IsoMatch or another loose-standing ISO-control box with a tractor equipped with the ISOBUS communication system, you can connect it with the supplied 7 points CAN cable to a standard tractor CAN connection."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the side of the cable to which 1 plug is attached to the tractor CAN connection."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the side of the cable to which 2 plugs are attached to both control box connections."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you use the IsoMatch or another loose-standing ISO-control box with a tractor that is not equipped with the ISOBUS communication system, you need a tractor ECU. Your dealer can supply this. This tractor ECU has an outgoing 9 point CAN plug."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the CAN-plug to the control box."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "39"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 40,
  "items": [
