    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only park with an empty hopper"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only park the machine on the parking wheels if the hopper is empty! Parking with a filled hopper results in reduced stability. Moreover, the wheels are not designed for heavy loads. Damages to the machine and physical injury can be caused."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A disconnected machine can easily be moved with the parking wheels."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Raise the machine to working height."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Secure the machine by placing adequate supports."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the frame on the machine as described in the spare parts manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Secure the wheels with the lock clips."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Caster wheels may be placed on the side of the frame. This prevents the crop from being damaged while spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreader is provided with 12 vanes of equal length and 4 shorter."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Grease the threaded rods of the vanes."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Hook the short vanes into the correct position (see illustration)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Then place the other two vanes into the other positions."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Press the vanes in well and put the lock nut in position."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the vanes on the other side in the same manner."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fasten the lock nuts (50NM)"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Even wear of the vanes"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The long vanes are positioned in groups of three."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The first vane considered in the direction of rotation of the disc will wear out most quickly."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP \uf034 Exchange the first vane after the fixed vane, and the short vane, over a period of time."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 After a subsequent period, exchange the foremost vane at that time with the central vane."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "As a result, the vanes will wear evenly and the spreading pattern will remain optimal."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "43"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Short vane"
    },
    {
