          "1": "1",
          "2": "1"
        },
        "Double": {
          "0": "",
          "1": "",
          "2": ""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "49"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 50,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Mounting the coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking the coupling shaft length"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "50"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The coupling shaft provided is too long for most types of tractors"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The coupling shaft must be cut to the correct length before connecting it to the tractor. A coupling shaft that is too long could lead to serious damage to the machine and the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the paragraph \u00bbChecking the coupling shaft length\u00ab below"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae and the below paragraph \u00bbShortening the coupling shaft\u00ab."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "During lifting and lowering of the power lift, the coupling shaft requires adequate space for:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sliding in and out,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sufficient overlap between the profiled tubes when driving the machine in the extreme operating angle of the coupling shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Put the machine on a supporting beam before moving in between the tractor and machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This will ensure that the machine cannot drop if the power lift should inadvertently be operated while you are between the tractor and machine. Without the support, a power lift that drops could wedge you in, resulting in possible serious physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The length of the coupling shaft and the shortening thereof must be done after the power lift has been connected, but before the coupling shaft has been connected."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lift the machine with the power lift until the PTO shaft and the machine drive axle are level."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is the shortest possible length between the two shafts."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on a supporting beam."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor engine off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the coupling shaft for it to be two halves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the loose tractor section of the coupling shaft to the tractor PTO shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the loose machine component of the coupling shaft to the drive axle."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Manually align the two coupling shaft halves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the length and adjust it as described below."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 51,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Shortening the coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before first use"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The profiled tubes must overlap as far as possible, with a minimum of 150 mm ."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The profiled tubes must however have at least 25 mm free clearance at the outer edges when the tractor PTO shaft and the machine drive axle are level."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Cut off the two profiled tubes to achieve the 25 mm clearance."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Deburr both ends."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Clean the coupling shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Shorten the protection sleeves by the same length."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Slide the coupling shaft halves into each other."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the coupling shaft of the machine and the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lift the machine with the power lift in the highest operating position."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Put the machine on a supporting beam before moving in between the tractor and machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This will ensure that the machine cannot drop if the power lift should inadvertently be operated while you are between the tractor and machine. Switch also the tractor engine off and remove the keys from the ignition. Without the support, a power lift that drops could wedge you in, resulting in possible serious physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The maximum operating angle of the coupling shaft is 30 \u00b0 when lifted and 30 \u00b0 when lowered.This is the maximum length between the PTO shaft and the machine drive axle."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on a supporting beam wit the power lift in the highest position."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the furthest working angle is less than 30 \u00b0 ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the overlap of the profiled tubes is still at least 150 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the tractor section."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Apply grease to the profiled tubes."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the protection sleeves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Slide the coupling shaft halves into each other."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the coupling shaft to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Always mount the check chains of the protection sleeves"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The check chains prevent the protection sleeves from rotating with the coupling shaft. Crop or pieces of clothing can be wound around rotating protection sleeves and cause material damage and possibly severe physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the check chains to both outer edges of the coupling shaft protective sleeves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the other ends of the chains to a fixed point of the tractor and machine respectively. System settings"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "51"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 52,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Neutralise the controls"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Control devices, e.g. ropes, hoses, etc. for remote actuation of devices such as cylinders, shall be guided and positioned in a way they never inadvertently release nor block desired movements/actuations! Unintentional movements can lead to serious injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting and disconnecting safely"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "There are risks of injury involved in connecting and disconnecting the machine. Work carefully:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a mobile machine must also be protected from rolling away while being connected,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the machine should only be connected and disconnected from the tractor on a firm, dry and flat surface so that the machine would not tilt and/or sink into the ground,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 ensure no other people are in the immediate vicinity of the tractor or the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 work in accordance with the guidelines provided in this user's manual"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a power lift that conforms with the regulations must be used,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 never stand between the tractor and machine while the power lift is operated externally while connecting or disconnecting the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the machine must only be connected to the points intended for that purpose,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the machine must only be connected or disconnected while the PTO shaft is off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 check the state of the machine in order to ensure that it can safely be operated and transported."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connecting or disconnecting the machine in an unsafe manner could lead to serious personal injury and damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Always mount the check chains of the protection sleeves"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The check chains prevent the protection sleeves from rotating with the coupling shaft. Crop or pieces of clothing can be wound around rotating protection sleeves and cause material damage and possibly severe physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the following points before the PTO shaft is attached. Has the coupling shaft:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 no damage, including the protection sleeves?"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 are there sufficient lubricants as prescribed?"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 is the prescribed overlap of the coupling shaft halves and protection sleeves, both in transport and in operating position?"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Are the protection sleeves attached with chains to a fixed point to guard against turning?"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "An unsafe or improperly mounted coupling shaft could lead to serious or deadly injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the coupling shaft does not comply with the points mentioned above, it must be replaced before using the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "52"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 53,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Selecting linkage pin height"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Preparation"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Stabiliser chain"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Front power lift"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "There is an option of two tension levels, depending on the height of the crop. The high hitch points are for normal use, the low hitch points are used if the maximum lifting height of the tractor is not sufficient to ensure that the spreading height is 75 cm above the crop."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The low hitch points are also used when fertilising high crops, which is known as top dressing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "For further adjustments with top dressing, see"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbSpreading height\u00ab on page 95."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The space between the spreader and the tractor is limited as far as possible in order to keep the centre of gravity as closely to the tractor as possible. This promotes stability and the road behaviour of the tractor. As a result the coupling shaft, hydraulic hoses and electric plugs must be connected first, followed by the power lift."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Move the tractor to the front of the spreader so that the catch hooks of the power lift are around 200 mm from the spreader (the maximum distance depends on the reach of the coupling shaft; the halves must always overlap each other)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Take the pressure off the hydraulic system of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Put the lower links of the tractor level with the machine linkage pins."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Compensate for any height difference with the lift rod adjustment of the power lift."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Adjust the stabiliser chains to make lateral movement of the lower links impossible."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the appropriate ball bearings to the linkage pins and the top."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Secure the linkage pins and top again."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only connect the machine to the front power lift if:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 it has sufficient lifting power,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 it falls within the same fixing category as the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 with linkage frame (optional extras) for tractors with power lift of Cat. 3 / 4,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the minimum and maximum load of the front and rear weight would not be exceeded,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the tractor has a closed cabin and proper air filters (active carbon filters)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "53"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 54,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Coupling the coupling shaft"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "54"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The coupling shaft provided is too long for most types of tractors"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The coupling shaft must be cut to the correct length before connecting it to the tractor. A coupling shaft that is too long could lead to serious damage to the machine and the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbChecking the coupling shaft length\u00ab on page 50 and"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbShortening the coupling shaft\u00ab on page 51."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the PTO shaft and the connector for dirt or damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Push in the safety lock on the connector."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Slide the connector on the PTO shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Release the safety lock."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the safety plate latches by moving the connector."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the check chains to both outer edges of the coupling shaft protection sleeves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the other ends of the chains to a fixed point of the tractor, respectively the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "During lifting and lowering of the power lift, the coupling shaft requires adequate space for:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sliding in and out,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sufficient overlap between the profiled tubes when driving the machine in the extreme operating angle of the coupling shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "TIP The maximum operating angle of the coupling shaft is 30 \u00b0 when lifted and 30 \u00b0 when lowered.The maximum distance allowed between the PTO shaft of the tractor and the driving axle of the machine is reached in this position. A greater working angle could damage the coupling shaft."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 55,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting hydraulic hoses"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "electric plugs"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In case your machine is equipped with the ExactLine/Hydraulic border spreading plate (accessory), you must connect the hydraulic hoses for operation."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the hydraulic quick coupling on the tractor for dirt. Clean if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the hose from the hose coupling support and check the quick coupling for dirt. Clean if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the quick coupling."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the hose so that it would not pinch or damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Regularly inspect the hydraulic system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbChecking the hydraulic system\u00ab on page 131."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connect electric plugs safely"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Connect the electric plugs correctly. Place the electric plugs and cables in such a way that they would not get pinched or damaged. Only use the electric stream as intended. Do not use the cigarette lighter."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the plugs and the connections on the tractor for dirt. Clean if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the electric plug(s) for the lights."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the ISOBUS communication plug."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the control box."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 by connecting an ISO plug, which has both CAN plugs on the one side of the cable, to the back of the control box and the CAN plug on the other side of the cable to the connection on the ISOBUS network of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Remove the CAN plug of the tractor ECU from the control box if the tractor is equipped with a tractor ECU."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the cables so that they would not get pinched during working activities."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "55"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 56,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting to the tractor"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connecting the power lift"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking and setting the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "56"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the decoupling ropes of the quick coupling"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The decoupling ropes must never be tense and must provide sufficient freedom for movement, even with the power lift in the lowest position as it could otherwise accidentally disconnect the quick coupling. Accidental disconnection could cause damage to the machine and may lead to personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Reverse carefully so that the catch hooks of the lower links are exactly under the ball bearings."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the quick coupling of the catch hooks with the release ropes."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the power lift until the ball bearings are correctly located in the catch hooks and close the quick coupling."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the catch hooks have locked correctly by lowering the power lift carefully."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the top link to the appropriate length and secure if possible."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the quick coupling of the catch hook with the release rope."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Let the catch hook fall over the ball bearing at the top and close the quick coupling."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the catch hook is correctly secured by pushing and pulling it."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always check the machine after connection and set it horizontally if required."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lift the spreader until it is lifted from the ground or ramp."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the locking system of the catch hooks of the lower links and the top link."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Make sure that the electric cables and hydraulic hoses do not get jammed. Lead them or tie them up in order to prevent dangerous situations. Make sure that there is sufficient space for movement when lifting or lowering the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Adjust the machine so that it is level with the lift rod adjustment."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the top link until the machine is standing horizontally."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lock the top link when that is possible."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 57,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Finding the correct data for setting the spreader"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Characteristics of the fertiliser"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Determine the type and pattern of the granules"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The data for the correct setting of your spreader can be found in the spreading charts in the spreading chart book and the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbOnline spreading chart service\u00ab on page 61."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading charts indicate what type of fertiliser is best suited to achieving a good distribution. Correct adjustment depends on the characteristics of the fertiliser, not the brand! Determine the characteristics of the fertiliser, therefore, and find the spreading chart with similar features. Use the chart, even if the brand of the fertiliser differs from the nearest comparable fertiliser!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Select the spreading chart based on the characteristics of the fertiliser and not on the brand!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In order to find the correct spreading chart in the spreading chart book, online spreading chart service on the website, or via the free application (App) on your mobile phones, you must collect the following physical properties of the fertiliser"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 type and pattern of the granules"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see the paragraph below,\u00bbDetermine the type and pattern of the granules\u00ab"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 distribution (= composition of granules of various sizes),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see paragraph \u00bbDetermining distribution\u00ab on page 59,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 similar weight,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbDetermining similar weight\u00ab on page 60."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Distribution is the most vital characteristic of the fertiliser when it comes to spreading. You can make the first selection from the (online) spreading charts based on the distribution. Never use a spreading chart for another type of fertiliser, even if the distribution is very similar! You can determine which spreading chart compares the best to the fertiliser you are using based on similar weight."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Select the type of fertiliser from the spreading chart that is closest to the type of fertiliser that you are using."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The characteristics of the various types of fertiliser are so far reaching that using a spreading chart for another type of fertiliser, even if the distribution is the same, could provide a bad spreading pattern and could harm the crop!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "57"
    }
  ]
}

