{
  "page_number": 59,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Determining distribution"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The distribution is the ratio of granules with different diameters. A distribution meter comes with every spreader. This meter has 4 sections, with seven parts. The seven have different mesh width that divide the fertiliser granules, based on their diameters."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Distribution of 0-70-30-0 indicates none of the granules has a diameter of less than 2.0 mm, 70% have a diameter between 2.0 - 3.3 mm, 30% have a diameter between 3.3 - 4.75 mm and none is larger than 4.75 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You should therefore do the following to determine the distribution of the fertiliser with the distribution meter:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the slot that reads 4.75 mm and close the other openings with the cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the distribution meter with the cover and keep it on its side."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Shake it for as long as no more smaller granules are falling through the sieves."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the distribution meter back up and read the content of each slot. The given percentages should add up to 100%. It could be necessary to round the readings off with small and round granules."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Repeat the steps above three times and then determine the average distribution."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP Fill the fraction meter from another part of the hopper in order to obtain a good average as the larger granules tend to roll to the outer part of the hopper."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP Clean the seven parts regularly in order to prevent them from getting blocked."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The last figure indicates how you can read the following distribution: 0-70-30-0"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Indication with regard to the distribution:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 If the diameter of 10% or more of the fertiliser granules is smaller than 2.0 mm the fertiliser type would be difficult to spread, especially with large working widths. This could result in a less than optimal distribution and could damage the crops."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 If the diameter of 80 - 100% of the fertiliser granules is between 2.0 and 4.75 mm, the fertiliser would be good to spread, irrespective of the size of the remaining granules."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 If the diameter of 20% or more of the fertiliser granules is greater than 4.75 mm it would be difficult for optimum distribution. This could lead to damage to the crops as the granules could make holes in the leaves of the crop."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "59"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 60,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Determining similar weight"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Finding the correct spreading chart"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "60"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The density is the weight (kg) of 1 litre of fertiliser and it is expressed as kg/litre or ton/m3."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The following material is required to determine the density:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 measuring beaker (supplied),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 scale (supplied)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae Refer to the scale manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Working method to determine similar weight:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Hang the empty and dry measuring beaker on the scale."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Press the scale to 0."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the measuring beaker."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Knock the measuring beaker 5 times on firm ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill up the measuring beaker."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Weigh the fertiliser."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Repeat the steps above three times in order to determine the average weight."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Density of at least 1 kg/l is desirable for a good distribution of the fertiliser. Lighter types of fertiliser would be more difficult to spread and the maximum working width would be limited."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "On the basis of the data you collected about your fertiliser, for the spreading chart of fertiliser with the best comparable properties and desired working width in the table of contents of your spreading chart book, or fill in the data through the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones. \uf0ae see paragraph \u00bbOnline spreading chart service\u00ab on the following page."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can find the settings for the spreader, based on the application rate and the driving speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See then paragraph \u00bbSetting the spreader\u00ab on page 62."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP the page indicated in the table of index of the spreading chart book indicates the settings for the smallest desirable working width. The spreading charts for larger working widths are on the pages that follow those."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 61,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Online spreading chart service"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "AutosetApp"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Telephone App"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Information about the settings of the spreader can be found in the"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "spreading chart book, but also via the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application for mobile phones with an iOs and/or Android operating system. This will also provide information about additional types of fertiliser that have been tested recently. You can make use of the online spreading chart service as an alternative to the spreading chart book. You must enter the characteristics of the fertiliser, your working width, application rate, driving speed and the type of fertiliser. You will then receive advice from the website for setting your spreader: dosing setting, discharge point, flowrate, vane combination and angle of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Methods for adjusting the spreader can be found at: \uf0ae chapter \u00bbSetting the spreader\u00ab on page 62."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Also check the advice given on the online spreading chart service. Do a calibration test to check the dosing setting. Then check the spreading pattern with a tray test."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSpreading pattern check (tray test)\u00ab on page 76."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can reach the spreading chart service as follows:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Go to the website of the Kverneland Group: http://www.Kvernelandspreadingcharts.com."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The various languages are given at the top of the page."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the spreading chart service and complete the details required."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The spreading chart service will then request that you select a product with comparable characteristics."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The spreading chart service will then indicate the settings for your spreader. Follow the working methods as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbSetting the spreader\u00ab on page 62."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "AutosetApp gives you the option to download these spreading charts to the IsoMatch Tellus terminal in order to set the spreader automatically. After choosing the desired fertiliser type, the working width, application rate, driving speed, dosing and discharge opening are transmitted to the spreader using the AutosetApp. The spreader then automatically gets the correct setting. Automatic adjustment of the discharge point only applies to GEOSPREAD spreaders. The same data may be transmitted to the spreader via the AutosetApp for the other weighing spreader models such as Exacta-CL EW and Exacta-TL(X). Except for the discharge opening, the spreader then has to be set manually."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using the Kverneland Group spreading charts application, you can easily find the right settings for your spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading charts application gives you immediate access to the most up-to-date test results of fertiliser."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In just a few steps, the application will lead you to the correct settings for your spreader, any time of the day, wherever you want for almost any type of fertiliser."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading chart application (App) can be downloaded free of charge through the Apple App Store and/or through the Google Play Store."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "61"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 62,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Setting the spreader"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "62"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and safety gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with the materials could lead to personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while adjusting the spreader. Work carefully while making adjustments:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you start with filling, adjusting or testing,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Never go underneath an elevated, unsecured spreader,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Comply carefully with the instructions."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protecting the environment"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spreading a too high dose of materials outside of the field edge, especially on water surface, creates a heavy burden on the environment. Protect the environment by applying a correct application rate in a correct working manner."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work with a closed cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser dust can blow indoors through open windows, doors or other openings. Moreover, the sound level is higher in an open cabin. It is therefore recommended to always work with a closed cabin with active carbon filters in the air inlets. Fertiliser dust and a high sound level can cause physical damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Set the spreader based on the details obtained from the correct spreading chart, the desired application rate (kg/ha) and the driving speed (km/h)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can find the methods for determining the correct spreading chart in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae the instruction manual of the software."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading chart page contains information about the fertiliser to which this chart relates. Here you will also find the settings you need to perform in respect of your spreader:"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 64,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working width"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The working width must be selected to set the spreader. This could for instance be the distance between the sprayer tramlines."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the spreading chart book, via the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones with an iOs and/or Android operating system, look for the page that shows the desired working width of the fertiliser type with the most similar properties."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Various types of fertiliser have a limited maximum working width. This is due to their physical qualities whereby they do not spread evenly over large working widths. If a working width is not given in the spreading charts, the relevant type of fertiliser cannot be spread evenly over that width."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you want to spread with a working width not given in the spreading charts, use the settings for the working width closest to the selected working width. For example: the settings given in the spreading chart for a required working width of 25 metres could, for instance, be approximated to 24 metres. Enter the actual working width into the control system so that the selected application rate is correctly distributed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The working width is adjusted with:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the correct connection point for the coupling shaft with the PTO speed and"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the discharge point."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The working width of the spreader is also determined by the chosen connection point for the coupling shaft on the central gearbox. Which terminal (turtle or hare) you need to use is listed in the (online) spreading chart and depends on the desired working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Detach the coupling shaft from the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the coupling shaft to the correct attachment point."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Coupling shaft connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "point"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "Slow/tortoise connection point"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "64"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 65,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Discharge point"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Inclination"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Angle indicator"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Angle indicator"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Modification during GEOCONTROL use"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "PTO shaft rpm"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is necessary to correctly set the discharge point in order to obtain a good spreading pattern and the correct working width. The point at which the granules or seeds come onto the spreading disc can be changed by setting the discharge point. The position of the discharge point combined with the position of the coupling shaft on the central gearbox, the PTO speed and the flowrate determines the spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The discharge point can be set between positions C to U . The correct settings are determined on the basis of the selected application rate and the required driving speed. The position that would most likely provide the best spreading pattern is given in the third column, Discharge Point , of the spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always check the accuracy of the discharge point by conducting spreading pattern tests (tray test)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see instructions in paragraph \u00bbSpreading pattern check (tray test)\u00ab on page 76."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the (online) spreading chart, look for the Hoek spreader symbol to get advice on the angle of your spreader. The spreader is normally in the horizontal position. It may be necessary to adjust the spreader's angle with large working widths or with top dressing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can set the correct angle by adjusting the top link. There is an indicator on the spreader which displays the angle of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP Set the spreader angle before you fill the hopper. It is easier to adjust the top link if the hopper is empty."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the position again after the hopper has been filled!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the inclination is at 4 o of 8 o , the spreader area slides further behind the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 In the machine data screen, increase the length B by 10% or 20% at 4 o or 8 o ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae Please refer to the software instruction manual for the procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The (online) spreading chart shows the rpm of the spreading discs as well as the rpm of the PTO shaft. The PTO speed is given, as well as the connection point to be used for the machine coupling shaft. You have to calculate the speed of the spreader discs. The actual RPM of the spreading discs is displayed on the control box screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The PTO shaft rpm often have to be adjusted with border spreading. When using the ExactLine and the border spreading plate, you can find the recommended PTO shaft rpm and associated spreading disc rpm in the spreading chart book, via the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones. Use the connection point shown in the spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "See paragraph \u00bbBorder spreading\u00ab on page 106."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "65"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 66,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Application rate"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Constant application rate"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control system can drive the spreader in three different ways:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 distribution that resembles the settings for the preset application rate must be determined under changing circumstances through automatic calibration and driving speed correction,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see the paragraph below,\u00bbConstant application rate\u00ab."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "with similar or lower application rates (< 40 kg/min) the fine application kit should be used,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbFine application\u00ab on page 67."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 with very low application rates on very uneven terrain, preset application rates must be checked manually to ensure that the correct dosing setting is being distributed, without automatic calibration but with driving speed correction,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 under changing circumstances location specific application rate driven by an external signal, through automatic calibration and driving speed correction,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbVariable, externally driven application rate\u00ab on page 72."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control system can spread an equal amount of fertiliser over the entire field. In doing so, the control system corrects changes in driving speed, while maintaining the option to adjust the application rate manually for over- or underdosing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control system can search for the correct dosing setting with the preset application rate through automatic calibration. The disadvantage is that the application rate for the second automatic calibration (= approx. 2 minutes) could differ markedly from the selected application rate. It is therefore strongly recommended that the starting values be taken from the spreading charts. This can be done in the 'Curve Calibration' screen. The control system calculates the discharge curve from the starting values. The control system corrects the spreader for changing circumstances, based on this curve, e.g. as a result of changes in driving speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbThe ISO control system\u00ab on page 30."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Look for the most comparable fertiliser type and the correct settings for the selected working width in the (online) spreading chart:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Read the setting of the dosing in the Dosing Setting column that goes with the selected application rate and driving speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The corresponding flowrate is given in the Kg/min column."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The given values are to be entered in the control system."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the selected application rate is not given in the spreading charts, use the settings that are the closest to the selected application rate. If the selected driving speed is not given, use the settings closest to the selected driving speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "66"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 67,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Fine application"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fine application handle Normal dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Fine application handle Normal dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fine application handle Fine application setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Fine application handle Fine application setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "All three dosing openings normally open uniformly with the selected application rate and the corresponding flowrate that you set. With a low application rate and/or a low driving speed the dosing openings are only opened a slight bit so that very little fertiliser would stream through the dosing openings of the spreader. This could easily cause blockage, which would lead to a bad spreading pattern and possible damage the crops."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "We therefore advise that you make use of the fine application if the flowrate is less than 40 kg/min ."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The flowrate with a specific working width, application rate and driving speed is given in the fourth column of the spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If very low application rates (less than 25 kg/ha) are to be distributed, e.g. only a few kilograms per hectare, the control system cannot perform automatic calibrations. The distributed weight is too small to accurately adjust the application rate."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Close 2 of the 3 dosing openings to prevent blockages. The remaining opening must be further opened as the application rate with the constant flowrate would be three times as much."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The handle to close 2 of the 3 fine dosing openings is located at the outside of the spreading disc, above a similar handle for the discharge point. You will find the indications on top of the fine application handle for the number of dosing openings: 3 open holes for standard dosing and 1 open hole and 2 thick holes for fine application."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Pull the hand-grip of the fine application lever out."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the fine application handle until the arrow on the hand-grip indicates the desired position."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Let go of the hand-grip and check if the fine application handle is locked."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the fine application lever on the other spreading disc in the same way to the same position."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "67"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 68,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Dosing setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Setting the spreader"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "68"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The dosing setting to be set can be:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Read from the relevant spreading chart when you want to spread at a lower application rate using the fine application kit and the symbol of the Fine application kit is indicated in the spreading chart. This is indicated by means of 1 open hole (dosing opening)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Determine an application rate not given as described in paragraph \u00bbDischarge point\u00abfrom page 65."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 To be calculated using the relevant spreading chart when you wish to spread at a lower application rate with the fine application kit, and the Fine application kit symbol is indicated in the spreading chart; it is indicated using 3 open holes (dosage opening)."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Calculation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "As 2 of the 3 dosing openings are closed the flowrate of the remaining dosing opening should be three times as much in order to obtain an even application rate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Read the Dosing Setting, Discharge Point and Flowrate from the spreading chart. Calculate the flowrate with the formula given below as required."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the selected application rate or driving speed is not indicated in the spreading chart the required flowrate can also be calculated as follows:"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "flowrate required (kg/min) ="
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Working width (m) x Driving speed (km/h) x Application rate (kg/ha)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "600"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use the letter given for setting the discharge point in the line of the spreading chart that most closely resembling the calculated flowrate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Multiply the flowrate (given in the Kg/min column or calculated) with a factor of 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Select the closest flowrate for the whole spreader in the Kg/min column."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Read off the relevant dosing setting or estimate it as closely as possible."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "NOTE \uf034 Do not use the discharge point indicated there !"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "NOTE \uf034 Do not use the discharge point indicated there !"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the given discharge point as described"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae in paragraph \u00bbDischarge point\u00ab on page 65."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Enter the dosing setting in the control system and determine the relevant flowrate by means of a manual calibration test, as described in the following paragraph."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also the example in paragraph \u00bbConstant application rate\u00ab on page 66."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 71,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Manual calibration test"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "support for the calibration container"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "support for the calibration container"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "support for the calibration"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "S"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Lock nut"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Lock nut"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "NOTE"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not empty the calibration container!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Rinsing the calibration container greatly improves the accuracy the calibration test. All parts of the calibration container where fertiliser, seeds or granules could remain would now be filled."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The calibration test can now start."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae Please refer to the software instruction manual for the procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "71"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "PTO shaft rotates after disengaging"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "After switching off the PTO shaft, danger could arise as the machine will continue running because of inertia. Keep a safe distance to the machine until the moving parts have come to a complete stop. Approaching the machine while it is rotating can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can check with a manual calibration test if the preset dosing setting reaches the selected flowrate."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The calibration test is normally performed on the left spreading disc. Perform the calibration test with a filled hopper. \uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbFilling\u00ab on page 73."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the right spreading disc by sliding the connector to the right. Secure the connector with a lock clip."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the vanes from the left spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Connect the coupling shaft to the coupling point on the machine shown in the relevant spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbCoupling shaft connection point\u00ab on page 64."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount the calibration container carefully on the left spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the calibration container with the settings knob so that the spreading disc does not touch the calibration container."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Weigh a large trough and place it under the discharging point of the calibration container."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close all the doors and windows in the cabin."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the control box on."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the right spreading disc off."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the PTO shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the left dosing unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Allow the spreader to spread for 5 seconds in order to 'rinse' the calibration container."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the PTO shaft and the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition, empty the trough and place it back under the discharge point of the calibration container."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 72,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Variable, externally driven application rate"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "S"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "RS 232 connection"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "72"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control system provides the options to distribute the same application rate all over the field and the option to spread a variable, externally driven application rate. This provides the option to spread as per requirements, e.g. through a nitrogen sensor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "An application rate that had been preset in the corresponding management system for the relevant field can also be entered through the GPS system."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae For the options and corresponding settings, see the user's manuals for the external system and the control box, e.g. the IsoMatch. The control system of the spreader in combination with the IsoMatch control box also transmits the application rate and working width used back to the external system."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The external system and the control system of a spreader with an IsoMatch control box communicate through a serial port with an RS 232 connection. This connection is located at the back of the control box. The occupation of pins in the 9-point RS 232 plug and the settings required are given in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae the user manual of the IsoMatch control box."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 73,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Filling"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You could come into contact with materials when filling the machine. Always wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves, shoes and goggles. Read and adhere to the additional safety instructions and the of the material producer. Contact with the materials could lead to injury. Contact your physician in such an event!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Chemical reactions caused by mixing fertilisers"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Mixing different types of fertiliser could lead to a chemical reaction whereby poisonous vapours, liquids or other materials could come about. Possible danger of explosion! This could lead to personal injury and damage to the crop and machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only mix different types of fertiliser if allowed by the manufacturer(s)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Chemical reactions could lead to damage to the machines and personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Read the safety instructions provided by the supplier"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and apply that. Protective clothing should be worn when necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Disregarding the safety instructions could result in personal injury and damage to the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use proper tools"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Great volumes of material is often handled during the filling process. Use proper tools such as lifting devices when moving and filling the machine. Keep legislation concerning working conditions in mind. Work carefully and responsibly. Inferior tools can cause serious inju-"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "ries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only fill mounted machines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never place a machine in the ground while filling it. Always keep it in the power lift of the tractor. The machine is designed to be loaded while in a suspended state. Never park a filled machine on the ground. Filling the machine while it is on the ground could lead to damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work with a closed cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser dust can blow indoors through open windows, doors or other openings. Moreover, the sound level is higher in an open cabin. It is therefore recommended to always work with a closed cabin with active carbon filters in the air inlets. Fertiliser dust and a high sound level can cause physical damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "73"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 74,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Most types of fertiliser attract water and can thereby form large chunks. These chunks can block the spreader or distort the spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When working under moist conditions, use a hopper cover that closes well."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Do not spread without a hopper cover under moist conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Never leave the fertiliser for a long period of time in the spreader. Chunks can also be formed through moisture in the air."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Always clean the spreader well after use, including the dosing openings and the discharge bushings."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can fill the spreader to the desired levels after it has been put in place. It is recommended that the machine be loaded while it is lifted 10 cm above the soil. If no activities need to be performed on top of the hopper, the height can be adjusted with the automatic filling system."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A load platform must be used if the distance between the hopper rim and the ground is more than 1250 mm while filling manually or with large bags. The filling height is given in"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbTechnical specifications\u00ab on page 36."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If a fixed loading platform is used, drive the machine to the platform. The distance between the machine and the platform must be a maximum of 200 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the machine at the desired level. The machine must not rest on the ground, but rather be lifted a minimum distance of 10 cm!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the dosing units are closed. Close them if necessary by pressing the stop key on the main screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The position of the dosing units is displayed in the main screen on the control box of the control system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system off."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close all the doors and windows in the cabin."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place wheel chocks in front of the wheels of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If a mobile loading platform is being used, place the loading platform at the spreader so that there would be a maximum distance of 200 mm between the two."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the hopper cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the sieve is closed and secured."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the machine to the desired level with the correct tools. Fill the hopper halves to the same level so that the both of them would run empty at the same time."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Loading height"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working method"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "74"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 75,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Work carefully while filling and take the regulations that apply to working conditions into consideration! Make sure no objects or tools fall into the hopper . as it could block or damage the spreader!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the hopper cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not exceed the maximum recommended weight! \uf0ae See also \u00bbTechnical specifications\u00ab on page 36. The machine has not been constructed to carry the additional weight. Keep the axle load, load capacity of the wheels and the total weight of the tractor in mind, as well as the minimum axle load of the tractor. \uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbCalculate the axle load with tractor-mounted"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "machines\u00ab on page 13."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION If the weight should increase the filled spreader could fall backwards! \uf034 Set the spreader level length wise after it has been filled."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the spreader is filled during the spreading process, e.g. from an auger riding alongside the vehicle the automatic calibration must be switched off. With automatic calibration the control system weighs the dispersed quantity of fertiliser (kg) within a certain time. It also checks these values in terms of the selected, preset application rate. The distributed quantity can therefore not be correctly weighed if the hopper is filled while spreading. The weight in the hopper could even increase during the measurement period. The correction performed by the control system would be inaccurate as a result, which could lead to crop damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "75"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 76,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading pattern check (tray test)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "76"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while adjusting the spreader. Work carefully:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you start with the adjustments,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "The test should be performed on your own. Operate the machine on your own!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Dangerous situations for other people could easily occur when the machine is turning and the test conducted. Contact with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protecting the environment"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spreading a too high dose of materials outside of the field edge, especially on water surface, creates a heavy burden on the environment. Protect the environment by applying a correct application rate in a correct working manner."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "PTO shaft rotates after disengaging"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "After switching off the PTO shaft, danger could arise as the machine will continue running because of inertia. Keep a safe distance to the machine until the moving parts have come to a complete stop. Approaching the machine while it is rotating can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work with a closed cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser dust can blow indoors through open windows, doors or other openings. Moreover, the sound level is higher in an open cabin. It is therefore recommended to always work with a closed cabin with active carbon filters in the air inlets. Fertiliser dust and a high sound level can cause physical damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A tray test checks the distribution of the fertiliser as the spreader distributes it. The results of this test will indicate if you can improve the settings of the spreader, thereby improving the distribution of fertiliser and limiting loss."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Tray tests can be performed by specialised companies, but it is also possible to perform this test on your own. You will have to purchase some materials for it, however."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "We recommend that you request a specialist company to perform the tray test as they can also provide you with advice and answer your questions."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 77,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "When to perform the tray test:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When using a fertiliser type that is not in the spreading chart book, via the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones with an iOs and/or Android operating system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When using a fertiliser type of which the distribution and density deviate from the values indicated in the spreading chart book, via the online spreading chart service on the website or via the free application (App) for mobile phones with an iOs and/or Android operating system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When using fertiliser of moderate quality."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Test should be carried out annually on the left and the right side to check the equal distribution of both spreading discs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 After each change to the spreading mechanism of the spreader or when parts are replaced."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Weather conditions have a great influence on the spreading pattern while spreading, as well as while performing the tray test. The tray test should be performed with dry weather, low humidity and with a maximum wind speed of 3 m/s (wind force of 2)."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Material required"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 measuring tape or ruler,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 spirit level to set the troughs horizontal,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 7 troughs,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 7 graduated tubes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 1 funnel,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 notebook, pen and calculator,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 this manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the instruction manual of the software."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "General instructions"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the preset dosing setting and the discharge point."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the height (75 cm above the troughs) and the position (angle) of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the rpm of the PTO shaft and the spreader discs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Always place the buckets horizontally on the floor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the buckets at a maximum distance of 4 metres. Provide additional widths for testing widths of more than 24 meters. Also, you can first test part of the working width and then empty the trays and distribute them over the rest of the working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Do not use the spreader while it is raining or with high humidity. This will cause the fertiliser to cling to the troughs, which would not provide the desired results."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Do not spread with wind speeds of more than 3 m/s (wind force of 2)."
    },
    {
