    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close all the doors and windows in the cabin."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the control box on."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Enter the required application rate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Enter the working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is recommended that an application rate of at least 250 kg/ha is entered with the selected driving speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch on the left spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the automatic calibration."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the PTO shaft and set the RPM of the spreading discs as given in the relevant spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the right dosing unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive over the first trough and stop only after you have driven at least 20 metres past this trough. This is because the spreader distributes roughly even to the back, front and to the side."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing unit."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Empty the trough with a funnel into the graduated tubes and record the reading in your notebook."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Repeat the above procedure, but disconnect the right spreading disc and switch the dosing unit of the right spreading disc off. Put the troughs on the left side of the tractor track."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Drive with the same speed and with the same PTO shaft rpm as with the first time!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "79"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 80,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Assessment"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Record the values you find in the graduated tubes for the left and right spreading discs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Compare the values, calculate the percentage differences between the measuring tubes on the left and the right."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Adaptation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the spreading patterns on the left and right spreading discs are not the same and the difference is greater than 3% you will have to do the following, or request your dealer to do so:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the machine is hanging horizontally and vertically behind the tractor in length and width."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the \u00bbChecking and setting the dosing mechanism\u00ab as described on page 133 and repeat the test."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the \u00bbChecking and setting the discharge point setting mechanism\u00ab as described on page 136 and repeat the test."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the difference in the spreading pattern is too great, contact your dealer."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "80"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 81,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Full field spreading pattern test"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the spreader is correctly set and the tramlines are set at the correct distance from each other you would achieve a good distribution of fertiliser over the land. This will only be achieved if the spreader spreads with the correct spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is then the reason why you have to test the spreading pattern and adjust it as required."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbFull field spreading pattern\u00ab on page 28."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the spreader as per the details given in the spreading chart for the selected working width (X metre) that most closely matches the fertiliser, seeds or granules (height of the spreading disc = 75 cm above the troughs) ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the grids in the troughs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place trough 1 in the middle of the tractor tracks."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION Position the troughs horizontally with a spirit level!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Divide the additional 6 buckets on the one side of the track over the actual working width of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The actual width is twice the size of the effective working width!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you want to spread over a working width of 24 metres, place the buckets at 24/6 metres = 4 metres."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "81"
    }
  ]
}

