  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Testing the spreading pattern of the hydraulic border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always perform a calibration test first and determine the correct dosing setting before checking the spreading pattern. Changes to the dosing setting will also have an influence on the spreading pattern! \uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSpreading pattern check (tray test)\u00ab on page 76."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When using the border spreading plate the aim is to obtain maximum distribution to the border with minimum loss in the ditch."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is then why the border spreading plate has to be tested. Do not perform this test next to the ditch, rather mark a line behind which the fictive ditch will be."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the right or left spreading disc by sliding the connector to the right or left. Secure the connector with a lock clip."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing unit of the right or left spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION Check that the vanes do not touch the border spreading plate!"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the spreader in accordance with the spreading chart for the desired working width and the instructions given in the 'One-sided boundary spreading\" chapter (height of the spreading disc = 75 cm above the troughs) ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place 1 trough in the middle of the tractor tracks. The centre of the driving track must be 2 metres from the line behind which the fictive ditch is located."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION Position the troughs horizontally with a spirit level!"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "INDICATION Position the troughs horizontally with a spirit level!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "84"
