      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place 1 trough on the land next to the fictive border ditch and 2 troughs next to each other in the fictive ditch."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor and engage the PTO shaft. The correct PTO shaft rpm is the standard value, less 25%, being 540 rpm - 25% = 400 rpm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Select a gear that would ensure that you drive at the same speed as with the normal PTO shaft, or reduce the application rate by 25%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start driving along the field edge. The distance between the border and the middle of the tractor must be 2 metres."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the dosing unit a few metres before you get to the middle bucket."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Only stop spreading after you have driven at least one working width over the troughs (e.g. 24 metres). This is because the spreader distributes roughly even to the back, front and to the side."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you set an application rate of less than 250 kg/ha, drive over the same tracks in order to collect sufficient fertiliser in the troughs for a good comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintain the same distance with opening and closing the dosing unit. Keep to the same driving speed and PTO shaft rpm!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Empty the troughs with a funnel into the graduated tubes."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A hydraulic border spreading plate is available for both sides."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the tap to prevent unintentional lifting of the plate while working."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close off the dosing on the side where no spreading is to be done."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 disconnect the drive of the plate on the side where no spreading is to be done."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the plate using the (online) spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintain the correct disc rpm when spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Set the plate more in the direction of position 9 to spread more towards the edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Set the plate more in the direction of position 1 to spread less towards the edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading chart shows settings for the yield and H2O positions; for the yield position use the standard mounted (short) plates."
