{
  "page_number": 88,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Testing the full field spreading pattern with the hydraulic border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Reducing the PTO shaft rpm and closing the right spreading disc also have an influence on the spreading pattern on the left side of the spreader. The full field spreading pattern should therefore be tested when using the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Follow the instructions, adjusted for border spreading, as described in \uf0ae paragraph \u00bbFull field spreading pattern test\u00ab on page 81."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Do not change the position of the border spreading plate and disconnect the right or left spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With the first time:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Do not change the settings of the spreader, the PTO shaft rpm or the driving speed as these should be the same as settings for border spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With the second time:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lift the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the spreader for full field spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the RPM of the spreading discs as given in the relevant spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The driving speed and PTO shaft rpm must be the same as the first time."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Assessment"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The middle buckets could contain less application rate. The pattern on illustration B from"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbFull field spreading pattern test\u00ab on page 81."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is because of the lower PTO shaft rpm."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The level of the middle measuring tube in border spreading could be 25% lower than with the outer graduated tubes."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Adaptation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the difference is more than 25%:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Increase the spreading disc rpm by 50 rpm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the full field spreading pattern test with the adjustments for border spreading again until the deviation is less than 25%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the spreading pattern test of the border spreading plate anew. Adjust the position of the border spreading plate until the loss is below the legal requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "88"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 89,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Testing ExactLine spreading pattern"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When using the ExactLine the aim is to obtain maximum distribution to the border with minimum loss in the ditch."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This is why the ExactLine has to be tested. Do not perform this test next to the ditch, rather mark a line behind which the fictive ditch will be."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the spreader as per the details given in the spreading chart for the selected working width that most closely matches the fertiliser, seeds or granules (height of the spreading disc = 75 cm above the troughs) ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Allow the hydraulic valve to run a few seconds to bring the ExactLine to working condition and to put good pressure in the accumulator."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the taps in the hydraulic hose to prevent the ExactLine from ending up in a different position by accident."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the ExactLine to the environment setting as per the details given in the spreading chart for the desired working width"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbBoundary track spreading with ExactLine\u00ab on page 110."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "89"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 90,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "To be done before spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place 1 trough on the land next to the fictive border ditch and 1 trough next to each other in the fictive ditch."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION:"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Position the troughs horizontally with a spirit level!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place 1 trough in the middle of the tractor tracks. The driving track must be half a working width from the fictive ditch. Divide the additional buckets between the track and the fictive ditch."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor and engage the control box."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close all the doors and windows in the cabin."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the PTO shaft and set the RPM of the spreading discs as per the spreading chart or based on the table in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you want, you can choose to accelerate so that you are driving at the same speed as during full field spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the automatic calibration."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive along the tracks and open the dosing units a few metres before you drive over the first bucket in the middle by pressing the start key."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Only stop spreading after you have driven at least one working width over the troughs (e.g. 18 or 24 metres). This is because the spreader distributes roughly even to the back, front and to the side."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing units."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you set an application rate of less than 250 kg/ha, drive over the same tracks in order to collect sufficient fertiliser in the troughs for a good comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintain the same distance with opening and closing the dosing units. Keep to the same driving speed and PTO shaft rpm!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Empty the troughs with a funnel into the graduated tubes."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "90"
    }
  ]
}

