      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Review and adaptation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The maximum acceptable loss in the ditch is determined by environmental standards. In order to comply with the standards the quantity of fertiliser in the 1st trough, standing in the imaginative ditch, must be a maximum of 10% of the quantity collected in the trough in the middle of the track (= 100%)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The trough on the land next to the fictive ditch provides an insight into the topping. It will never be 100%."
    },
    {
      "type": "TableItem",
      "table_data": {
        "A": {
          "0": "B",
          "1": "",
          "2": "C"
        },
        "Good spreading pattern, the ExactLine has been adjusted  well": {
          "0": "The ExactLine is not spreading wide enough. \uf034 transport setting) \uf034 Repeat the test",
          "1": "Adjust this 1 setting wider (e.g. from 3 to 4 or from 7 to",
          "2": "The ExactLine is spreading too wide: \uf034 Adjust this 1 setting narrower (e.g. from 5 to 4 or from  transport setting to 7) \uf034 Repeat the test"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you adjust the ExactLine 1 setting higher or lower (e.g. from 1 to 2, or from 3 to 2), the working width on the side of the ditch changes roughly 0,3 metres."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Setting the spreading height back to the tray test"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "During the tray test the disc height above the troughs was set to 75 cm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Imagine spreading with the disc height at 75 cm above the ground or crops!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSpreading height\u00ab on page 95."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "91"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 92,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Driving on the road"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Driving on the road"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Before taking the road"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "92"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Observe the permissible and safe height with regard to"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 prescribed maximum height for vehicles in the road traffic regulations,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 high-voltage cables or other cables over the road;"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 anticipated maximum headroom."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Pay close attention to these aspects to prevent dangerous situations that could lead to major material damage and possibly to serious physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Before leaving the tractor:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the PTO shaft off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 release the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the electronic control system off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "That way you make sure that the tractor cannot be started when you are working on the machine and that the machine cannot move, which could cause severe physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before travelling on a public road with your tractor and machine, you should do the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check whether tractor and machine are roadworthy."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the lights, warning indicators, protectors and brakes are attached properly and are working."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check whether the reflector, motor vehicle with limited speed (<40km/h) on your tractor, is hidden by the implement."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Then fit an additional reflector at the back of the implement."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the run of the quick coupling ropes of the power lift."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 93,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Preparing the machine to be transported"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Driving on the road"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before travelling on a public road with your tractor and machine, you should do the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check whether tractor and machine are roadworthy."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the lights, warning indicators, protectors and brakes are attached properly and are working."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the run of the quick coupling ropes of the power lift."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fit extra lighting and warning signs, if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check all folding parts and their locking devices:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 hopper cover,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 hydraulic border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set all parts of the machine and the tractor, especially the PTO shaft, the hydraulics, the wheels and the electric system, to transport mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the weight distribution between front and rear axles."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount front weights, if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the headroom of the combination."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the power lift, if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lock the control lever of the power lift while moving so that the machine is not lowered by accident."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the lights are in good working order."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check whether the dosing units are closed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the control box."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove dirt that could fall off while on the road. A dirty road could be hazardous for other drivers."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Control devices, e.g. ropes, hoses, etc. for remote actuation of devices such as cylinders, shall be guided and positioned in a way they never inadvertently release nor block desired movements/actuations!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Always ensure adequate lateral securing of a mounted machine in transport position."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "93"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 94,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "94"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Friction between moving parts"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Be careful of moving parts making contact with each other while working. You could accidentally touch control levers and cause the machine to move."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only start working once all machine parts have stopped and the control lever have been secured. Wear safety shoes and gloves and work alone. If something gets jammed it could lead to personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the immediate vicinity and keep a constant eye on it at the start, as well as while you are working with the machine. Familiarise yourself with the immediate vicinity. Do not start working until all people and obstacles within the working area and danger zone of the tractor and machine have been removed."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never stay or allow anyone to stay within the danger area while the machine is running! If there are people within the working area and the danger zone it could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Before leaving the tractor:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the PTO shaft off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 release the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the electronic control system off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "That way you make sure that the tractor cannot be started when you are working on the machine and that the machine cannot move, which could cause severe physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "PTO shaft rotates after disengaging"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "After switching off the PTO shaft, danger could arise as the machine will continue running because of inertia. Keep a safe distance to the machine until the moving parts have come to a complete stop. Approaching the machine while it is rotating can cause serious or deadly injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protecting the environment"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spreading a too high dose of materials outside of the field edge, especially on water surface, creates a heavy burden on the environment. Protect the environment by applying a correct application rate in a correct working manner."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work with a closed cabin"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser dust can blow indoors through open windows, doors or other openings. Moreover, the sound level is higher in an open cabin. It is therefore recommended to always work with a closed cabin with active carbon filters in the air inlets. Fertiliser dust and a high sound level can cause physical damage."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 95,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Adjusting the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading height"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Ground level or the top level of the crops"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Ground level or the top level of the crops"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Most types of fertiliser attract water and can thereby form large chunks. These chunks can block the spreader or distort the spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When working under moist weather conditions, use a hopper cover that closes well."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Do not spread without a hopper cover under moist conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Never leave the fertiliser for a long period of time in the spreader. Chunks can also be formed through moisture in the air."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Always clean the spreader well after use, including the dosing openings and the discharge bushings."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before you can make the first pass, you must make adjustments in the field to:"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The following is important to ensure that the spreader works properly:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 set it to the correct height from the ground or above the crop and"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 by levelling it with the lift rod adjustment and top link."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Measured from the bottom of the vanes, the distance to the ground or the crop must be 75 cm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Use the power lift to lift the machine to the correct height."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the spreader horizontally with the lift rod adjustment and the top link."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lock the lift limiter in this position."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Height correction with top dressing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the required height of 75 cm above the crop is not possible with your power lift"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 use the high spreading setting of the linkage pins and/or"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 set the spreader forward as indicated in the spreading charts."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSelecting linkage pin height\u00ab on page 53."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "95"
    }
  ]
}

{
