{
  "page_number": 97,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading on field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading on the headland"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Filling passes"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Set tramlines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working with the GEOCONTROL"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Starting a new task is done from a saved field or one to be created newly with the GEOCONTROL application."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae Refer to the GEOCONTROL manual in your terminal for this purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A broad headland is desirable in order to make the connection to the headland before turning in from the pass. The headland will act as the field boundary and is saved in GEOCONTROL."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A broad headland is desirable in order to make the connection to the headland before turning in from the pass."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Spread a broad or double headland so that you make the connection while driving straight before making a turn."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Thereafter, the field can be filled in full passes. You can create a (spray)track pattern for following processes."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Prevent drive errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is important that the spreading patterns overlap well to ensure good distribution. A difference in the overlapping is less vital with average working widths, using a triangular spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Differences in the spreading pattern would easily be noticed with a trapezium shape on very large working widths, in particular. The overlap of the spreading pattern is then much smaller and therefore more sensitive to mistakes."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This can be prevented by setting tramlines before hand. This can be done by setting out tramlines on the headlands and marking them with, for example, picket poles."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Visibility of the from headland to headland is very important. Place additional markers in the field if necessary to ensure that the track is clearly visible."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When controlled by the GEOCONTROL the spreader has the option of reducing the working width in order to connect the incomplete final pass with the next one."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "97"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 98,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Tramline patterns"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using the ExactLine with tramlines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "98"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Your preferred border spreading method determines the tramline pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Select on the basis of the site width, the presence of the spreader tramlines and the spreader's equipment."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Drive half the working width from the field edge (1/2 X meters) when doing boundary track spreading with ExactLine (optional extra)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the first way at half the working width (1/2 X meter) from the field edge (in the first sprayer tramline)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 The paths that follow are set at the full working width."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbBoundary track spreading with ExactLine\u00ab on page 110."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP: Indicate whether the field boundary is to the right of the machine while spreading the headland in the GEOCONTROL!"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 99,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using the hydraulic border spreading plate with tramlines"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "During one-sided boundary spreading with hydraulic border spreading plate, you drive along the outermost work area on the field edge and control the fertiliser granule stream by means of the hydraulic border spreading plate (accessory)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The paths that follow are set at:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 half the working width of Situation A (the first sprayer tramline),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the complete working width Situation B."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbOne-sided boundary spreading with the hydraulic border spreading plate\u00ab on page 107."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP: Indicate that the field boundary is to the right of the machine while spreading the headland in the GEOCONTROL!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "99"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 100,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Start spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Connect headland with the GEOCONTROL function"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Overlap on the headland"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Overlap on the field boundary"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "100"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To begin spreading, proceed as follows:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close all the doors and windows in the cabin."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive the tractor to the first tramline, depending on the driving pattern required, which may be recognised by the marker in place."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the control box on."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the settings as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Without GEOCONTROL, select and activate a site number in the field registration,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch on the PTO shaft and set the correct spreading disc rpm as reported in the spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not allow the spreading disc to run for longer than is necessary while the dosing units are closed. This will prevent the agitator from grinding the fertiliser."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start driving and open the dosing units at the same time by pressing the start key."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The rpm of the tractor engine (therefore also of the PTO shaft) must remain constant while spreading (with regards to distributing fertiliser along the width)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The driving speed can only be adjusted by selecting another speed!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Based on the offset set in the 'TC Implement Settings' screen, the GEOCONTROL will switch the spreading sections off by itself when passing the headland limit. This happens if the spreading pattern overlaps completely and you run up the headland."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Depending on the set overlap percentage, the connection on the headland and gores will more or less overlap."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The usual setting is 50%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the GEOCONTROL manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Even the extent of overlap of the field boundary created can be separately set in the GEOCONTROL manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP Set the overlap on the field boundary to 0 if you do not wish to spread over the field boundary."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 101,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "approaching headland with the GEOCONTROL function switched off:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing units by pressing the stop key before turning to the headland. The PTO shaft can keep running if you intend to start spreading immediately again."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will find the correct working method and corresponding distances on the headland in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae the next paragraph \u00bbWorking method on the headland\u00ab and paragraph \u00bbSpreading on field\u00ab from page 97."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive to the next tramline and re-start the spreader at the right time, as displayed in the next paragraph \u00bbWorking method on the headland\u00ab."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the event of spreader failure or stoppage:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Stop spreading immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the PTO shaft immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See then paragraph \u00bbFailure and stoppage\u00ab on page 113."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the hopper content becomes less than 100 kg, the control system switches off the automatic calibration. Measurement accuracy declines in such a way that new automatic calibration cannot produce a better discharge curve."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "At low doses <50 kg/ha, it is possible to reduce the minimum hopper capacity for automatic calibration to minus 15 kg."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the spreader is filled during the spreading process, e.g. from an auger riding alongside the vehicle the automatic calibration must be switched off. With automatic calibration the control system weighs the dispersed quantity of fertiliser (kg) within a certain time. It also checks these values in terms of the selected, preset application rate. The distributed quantity can therefore not be correctly weighed if the hopper is filled while spreading. The weight in the hopper could even increase during the measurement period. The correction performed by the control system would be inaccurate as a result, which could lead to crop damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "101"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 102,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working method on the headland"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "102"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The driving pattern that you use, in other words how you must turn on the headland, depends on your border spreading method."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 spreading the border from the sprayer tramline with ExactLine, one-sided boundary spreading with additional room with the border spreading plate (situation A), or"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 border spreading by closing off one disc and using a border spreading plate (situation B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do the following when spreading the headland:"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "For boundary track spreading from the sprayer tramline (ExactLine and situation A)"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "GEOCONTROL headland function ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Begin with creating the field boundary where you spread on edges with the ExactLine while driving to the left through the first sprayer tramline."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Make a second round with the ExactLine switched off for a double headland, if required."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the field with injections on your sprayer tramline defined previously."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The GEOCONTROL will itself determine the correct start/stop moment while approaching and turning from the spread headland."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 103,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Hydraulic border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the field boundary as close as possible along the field boundary while driving to the left or to the right, to spread right down to the border with the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the headland through to half the working width without the border spreading plate with the right/left dosing closed to make an additional pass."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See \u00bbOne-sided boundary spreading with the hydraulic border spreading plate\u00ab on page 107."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the field with injections on your sprayer tramline defined previously."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The GEOCONTROL will itself determine the correct start/stop moment while approaching and turning from the spread headland."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Spreading without GEOCONTROL headland:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Stop spreading by closing the dosing units of the machine when you are half a working width from the end of the land."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Let the spreading discs turns and do not switch off the PTO shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the dosing units again at one and a half the working width of the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Finally spread the field edges with the ExactLine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbBorder spreading\u00ab on page 106."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "With one-sided border spreading (situation B)"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "103"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 104,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "GEOCONTROL headland function"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "104"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Begin with creating the field boundary where you spread down to the border along the field boundary while driving to the left/right with the border spreading plate and the right/left dosing switched off."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the field with injections on your sprayer tramline defined previously."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The GEOCONTROL will interrupt and start the process at the correct time while turning on the headland."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Without GEOCONTROL"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive as closely as possible to the end of the property and stop spreading by closing the dosing units before you turn."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Let the spreading discs turns and do not switch off the PTO shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the dosing units again when you are a full working width down from the end of the land."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Finally spread the field edges with the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbBorder spreading\u00ab on page 106."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 105,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Over and underdosing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Results of one-sided over- or underdosing"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Depending on soil or crop composition, it is preferable to spread more or less fertiliser locally. With the control system, you can over- or under dose to the left, right or on both sides during spreading. You will find all the control keys on the main screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreading pattern of both spreading discs overlap partially, especially in the middle behind the spreader. For this reason, the real application rate will deviate from the one that you set during one-sided over- and under dosing. You will see the effect especially with narrow working widths because that is when the spreading patterns overlap the most."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "With small working widths in which you spread in a triangular spreading pattern, the first and second passes of the spreading patterns overlap each other completely."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbSpreading pattern\u00ab on page 28. To distribute an adjusted application rate you must therefore over- or underdose on the first as well as the second pass in the following tramline."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "105"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 106,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Border spreading"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "106"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spreading fertiliser up to the border of the property requires concentration. On the one hand you want to achieve maximum cover to the field edge to ensure a good crop, while on the other hand you want to minimise the loss over the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The spreader has 2 different functions and accessories to cater for border spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 one-sided boundary spreading with the hydraulic border spreading plate,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 boundary track spreading with ExactLine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When one-sided boundary spreading, drive with the tractor along the field edge and spread from the border inwards. With boundary track spreading, drive down the first sprayer tramline from the field edge and spray in the direction of the border."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "We advise you to spread the site first before you spread the borders. During border spreading, the control system does not perform any automatic calibration, so it cannot accurately determine the correct dosing setting for the required application rate. Consequently, the application rate can deviate from the required application rate during border spreading. By spreading the field first, the control system can determine the correct dosing setting and thus spread at the correct application rate, also during border spreading."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 107,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "One-sided boundary spreading with the hydraulic border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Drive along the field edge when one-sided boundary spreading and send the flow of fertiliser granules with the hydraulic border spreading plate (optional extra). The working width on the side of the field edge can be adjusted by changing the hydraulic border spreading plate (optional extra)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Direction ( 1 ) (environmental set- ting)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spread less to the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "This will decrease the loss over the field edge, but the cover will not be as good"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Direction ( 9 ) (yield setting)"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spread more to the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Cover is better, but the loss is greater"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The maximum acceptable loss over the field edge is determined by environment standards. In order to comply with the standard the quantity of fertiliser spread beyond the field edge must be a maximum of 10% of the quantity distributed in the centre behind the spreader (= 100%). Test if the border spreading plate (optional extra) door de test therefore always before hand as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbTesting the spreading pattern of the hydraulic border spreading plate\u00ab on page 84."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "107"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 108,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Procedure with hydraulic border spreading plate"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "108"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Left and right border spreading is possible with the hydraulic border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the right spreading disc by sliding the connector to the right. Secure the connector with a lock clip."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the border plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the vanes do not touch the border spreading plate!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Adjust the spreader based on the details given in the spreading chart for the desired working width. Use the same settings and coupling shaft mounting point as with full field spreading,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See also paragraph \u00bbSetting the spreader\u00ab on page 62."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the control box on."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the PTO shaft. The correct rpm of the spreading discs is the value of the relevant spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you want, you can choose to accelerate so that you are driving at the same speed as during full field spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The control system will drive the dosing units in such a way that the actual application rate is equal to the set application rate through the lower PTO shaft RPM."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the event of spreader failure or stoppage:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Stop spreading immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the PTO shaft immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See then paragraph \u00bbFailure and stoppage\u00ab on page 113."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "After border spreading:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lift the border spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Reconnect the drive of the right spreading disc."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 109,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Driving pattern"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Two different driving patterns can be used, depending on the situation on your land."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working from the sprayer tramlines (situation A):"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive the first path with the middle of the tractor about 2 metres from the field edge. Decrease the PTO shaft rpm to 75%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the border spreading plate at the end of the first pass or raise the hydraulic border spreading plate, but disconnect the right spreading disc and close the dosing unit,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see the methods above."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Increase the PTO shaft rpm to 100% again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive down the second path in the first sprayer tramline."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 After the second operation, link up the right spreading disc drive again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the dosing unit of the right spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working without sprayer tramlines (situation B):"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive the first path with the middle of the tractor about 2 metres from the field edge. Decrease the PTO shaft rpm to 75%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the border spreading plate at the end of the first pass or raise the hydraulic spreading plate."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Reconnect the drive of the right spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the dosing unit of the right spreading disc."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive up the second line 1 working width from the field edge (X metres). Maintain the distance with the field edge carefully by using pickets, for instance."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "109"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 110,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Boundary track spreading with ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Operation"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "ExactLine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "110"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Drive half the working width from the field edge (1/2 X meters) (=first sprayer tramline) when doing boundary track spreading with the ExactLine (accessory). The flow of fertiliser granules, seeds or other granules spread with ExactLine. The working width on the side of the field edge can be adjusted by changing the ExactLine position."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The maximum acceptable loss over the field edge is determined by environment standards. In order to comply with the standard the quantity of fertiliser spread beyond the field edge must be a maximum of 10% of the quantity distributed in the centre behind the spreader (= 100%). Test the ExactLine therefore always in advance as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbTesting ExactLine spreading pattern\u00ab on page 89."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The (online) spreading charts indicate the correct setting for the ExactLine and the relevant rpm for the PTO shaft and the spreading discs."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the settings of the ExactLine are not given in the relevant spreading chart they can be obtained in the following sources:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 find with the online spreading chart service on the website or via the Free Application (App) for mobile phones with an iOs and/or Android operating system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbOnline spreading chart service\u00ab on page 61."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always check the settings of the ExactLine by performing the test as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbTesting ExactLine spreading pattern\u00ab on page 89."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The type of fertiliser is determined when adjusting the spreader, as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbDetermine the type and pattern of the granules\u00ab on page 57."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "you can choose from 3 settings from the chart:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 YIELD."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 ECO,"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the yield setting (YIELD), the loss over the field edge is higher than what is allowed by the environmental standard. Therefore, never use this setting next to surface water. Cover to the border is very good with this option."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The loss over the field edge will be equal to or less than the environment standard in the environment setting (ECO). Always use this setting when working next to a surface water! The result is that the cover at the border of the property is not optimum."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 111,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working method"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Accumulator"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the ExactLine by letting the relevant single-acting hydraulic valve run for a few seconds. This is also how pressure is built in the accumulator. You will see the ExactLine symbol on the main screen. The symbol only appears when the ExactLine is in working position."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the tap on the hydraulic hose to prevent the ExactLine from changing position while spreading due to a leaking tractor valve."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Do not change the settings of the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbSetting the spreader\u00ab on page 62."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the ExactLine to the required position, based on the spreading chart, online spreading chart."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor and set the correct PTO shaft and spreading discs RPM, based on the spreading chart, online spreading chart or the chart on the previous page."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you want, you can choose to accelerate so that you are driving at the same speed as during full field spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Continue operating the spreader in the same way as in full field spreading,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbStart spreading\u00ab on page 100."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check regularly while spreading to see if the symbol of the ExactLine remains on screen. If the symbol disappears the ExactLine is no longer in a good working position."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Set the ExactLine back to transport mode after use by opening the tap in the hydraulic hose and then opening the relevant single-acting hydraulic valve for a few seconds."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The ExactLine's position is displayed on the main screen if you have connected this function."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "In this way, you will make fewer spreading errors caused by an incorrectly positioned ExactLine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "In the event of spreader failure or stoppage:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Stop spreading immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the PTO shaft immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See then paragraph \u00bbFailure and stoppage\u00ab on page 113."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "111"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 112,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Driving pattern"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When using the ExactLine, drive in the first sprayer tramline or half the working width (1/2 X meter) from the field edge."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Stopping work"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "112"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Right after working with the machine, before you leave, you must do the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the dosing units."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the pto shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system off."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove remains from the crop, dirt and stones from the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fix the hopper cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Take all appropriate measures for road transport."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbPreparing the machine to be transported\u00ab on page 93."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 113,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Failure and stoppage"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Causes"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is also easy to get injured while working with the spreader. Work safely with the machine:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you approach it,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "While working with the spreader, you might come into contact with fertiliser or other substances that you want to spread. Wear protective clothing and gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "During spreading, if you:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 see that a spreading disc is spreading irregularly or not at all while the dosing units are open,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 hear a loud noise,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 become aware that the machine is vibrating seriously,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 an alarm is shown on the main screen indicating that the PTO shaft is not connected, while it actually is connected,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 an alarm will appear on the main screen, indicating that the dosing units cannot be closed,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae see the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Stop spreading immediately! Disconnect the PTO shaft immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "113"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 114,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Working method"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "114"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "These failures are probably caused by one of the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a hard object blocks the agitator,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a hard object or a large piece of fertiliser is (partially) blocking the supply from flowing to the agitator,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a hard object or a large piece of fertiliser is (partially) blocking fertiliser from flowing through the dosing opening or discharge bushing,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 crushed and/or damp fertiliser forms an encrusted layer beneath the agitator and blocks the flow through the dosing openings,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 a lump of damp fertiliser has formed in the discharge bushing and is blocking flow from the discharge bushing opening. This happens especially when the spreader has not been thoroughly cleaned after it was last used."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Most types of fertiliser attract water and can thereby form large chunks. These chunks can block the spreader or distort the spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 When working under moist conditions, use a hopper cover that closes well."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Do not spread without a hopper cover under moist conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Never leave the fertiliser for a long period of time in the spreader. Chunks can also be formed through moisture in the air."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 Always clean the spreader well after use, including the dosing openings and the discharge bushings."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Handle with care"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Cautiously approach the machine and handle with care. There could be hot or live parts! Contact with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "To find the cause of the failure or stoppage and solve it as far as possible, proceed as follows."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the PTO shaft immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the electronic control system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the handbrake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not place the machine on the ground. Placing a filled machine on the ground damages the structure!"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 115,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Damage"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Close the sieve"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Examine the spreading discs and the discharge opening to see what the cause of the failure/stoppage is."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Adapt the discharge point as needed for easier access."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If you still cannot see the cause, carefully remove the vanes to see better into the discharge opening of the discharge bushing."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Pass an object such as a screwdriver through the discharge opening and carefully feel if you can find an object in or damage to the dosing openings or agitator."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you see damage to the vanes, spreading disc or discharge bushing, the failure is most likely caused by a hard object. The agitator is probably damaged too. You must first repair the damage or have it repaired before continuing with spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place an object, for example a cloth or bag, in the discharge opening of the discharge bushing on the damaged side. . This will prevent you from wasting fertiliser during transport."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor and engage the control box. The dosing units will now close."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the control box."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Take all appropriate measures for road transport."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbPreparing the machine to be transported\u00ab on page 93."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "On the site of a lockable storage depot:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Empty the hopper without positioning the machine on the ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the sieve closure with an attachment, standard supplied with the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Lock the sieve in the open position"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you open the sieves, you should lock them to prevent unwanted closing. Accidental closure could lead to serious injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the object that caused the damage."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Repair the machine or have your dealer do it."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "115"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 116,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Use in the field"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "stoppage"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Close the sieve"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Locking the opened sieve"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Close the sieveLocking the opened sieve"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Sieve clip locked"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Sieve clip locked"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "116"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you have not found any damage, the failure is probably due to stoppage from an encrusted layer of fertiliser."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Try to reduce the size of the lump or encrusted layer with an object such as a stick, screwdriver or vane."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you open the filters to reduce the lump or encrusted layer from the top side, you should block them to prevent unwanted closing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you can reduce the lump or encrusted layer in this way:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Inspect the hopper contents for other lumps and reduce them."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fit the vanes and secure them with the lock nut."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the discharge point setting."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the hopper cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Continue spreading."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you have not managed to reduce the lump or encrusted layer because it is out of reach or there is no tool at your disposal:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the hopper cover."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Follow the working method as described in the previous paragraph \u00bbDamage\u00ab until emptying the hopper."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove or reduce the lump or encrusted layer."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If necessary, dry the hopper and the dosing mechanism."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Opening the sieve clip"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the sieve closure with an attachment, standard supplied with the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lock the sieve to prevent it from closing accidentally."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the sieves and check the lock."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Refill the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the fertiliser for lumps before and after filling."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the hopper cover."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 117,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy to come into contact with the materials when putting away the machine. Always wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves, shoes and goggles. Read and adhere to the additional safety instructions and the of the material producer. Contact with the materials could lead to injury. Contact your physician in such an event!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is also easy to get injured while working with the spreader. Work safely with the machine:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you approach it,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Protect the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser and other salts have a great influence on the rate of corrosion. Empty the hopper at the end of activities. Protect the machine by always cleaning it after using such material and patch breaks in the paint. Corrosion affects the strength of the construction and the operation of the machine, which could lead to a shortened lifespan. After cleaning, inject the (white) metal parts of the machine with the supplied preserving liquid point for protection against corrosion of the"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "machine, read the instructions before use."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful while cleaning with high pressure cleaners"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can clean the machine with water or steam, possibly using only suitable cleaning tools. Also read here and adhere to the safety instructions of the material manufacturer."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Only use low pressure and temperature; 80 bar and maximum 40 o C."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Keep the nozzle more than 30 cm clear of turning parts, sensors, parts of the electric system, hydraulic hoses, stickers and plastic parts."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Only spray perpendicular to sticker edges."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Waste storage and disposal"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The waste water from cleaning the machine is contaminated with fertiliser and possibly also with lubrications. Collect the waste and dispose of it in terms of national regulations."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "117"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 118,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Cleaning"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "118"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is advisable to first lubricate, clean and again lubricate the machine before storing it for a short or longer period of time. If it is lubricated first you will prevent dirt, fertiliser and water from entering the bearings. After cleaning, grease and oil all items once again for conservation."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The advantages of this working order are:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 additional checks on the machine right after work,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 ensuring the longevity of the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 less delays due to problems while working with the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lubricate the machine grease nipples."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbLubricating points\u00ab on page 126."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Clean the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lubricate the machine grease nipples once again."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "When using a high-pressure cleaner, do not aim it at the seals and the breathers. That way you will prevent dirt and moisture from entering the gearboxes."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Furthermore, do not set up electrical components. Water can cause electrical failures."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 119,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Disconnecting the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Disconnect safely"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You may only disconnect the machine when"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 all parts are in a safe condition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 your immediate vicinity is safe,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the hopper is empty."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work carefully:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 check the environment (children!) and ensure that nobody is in the vicinity of the tractor or the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the machine or parking support must only be placed on a straight, firm surface,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 never stand between the tractor and machine while the power lift is operated externally while disconnecting the machine. Using the power lift entails the risk of accidents by crushing or jack-knifing,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 operate the power lift slowly and carefully,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the power lift during disconnection must be placed in such a position that accidental release or lowering would be eliminated,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 sufficient distance must be maintained between parts (e.g. parking support) that rest on the ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Working unsafely could cause serious injuries."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Proceed as follows to store the machine in stable condition for a shorter or longer period."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch off the pto shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the ExactLine hydraulic hose tap is closed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the ExactLine hydraulic hose tap of the hydraulic border spreading plate is closed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Take the pressure off the hydraulic system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on a stable, level base."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system off."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Adjust the length of the top link in such a way that it is no longer live."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Release the top link by undoing the release rope from the catch hooks and pulling the top link up."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Release the lower links by undoing the release ropes from the catch hooks and lowering the power lift as far as possible."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "119"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 120,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "TIP If you cannot lower the power lift far enough to release the catch hooks, we advise you to place the spreader on a firm, stable ramp, for example a pawl."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive the tractor about 200 mm forward (maximum distance depends on the range of the coupling shaft; the halves must always overlap each other)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Put wheel chocks in place to ensure that a machine equipped with parking wheels would not roll away."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the electric plugs and hang them in the container."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the hydraulic hoses."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the protective caps on the hydraulic hose connections."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Hang the hydraulic hoses in the hose coupling support."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disconnect the coupling shaft and hook it up."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the machine is equipped with parking wheels:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Drive the machine to the desired parking place."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place wheel chocks in front of the parking wheels."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Container for electrical plugs and hydraulic hoses"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "120"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 121,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Preparation for winter storage"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Storing the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "At the end of the season the machine must be prepared for winter storage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is advisable to first lubricate, clean and again lubricate the machine before storing it for a short or longer period of time. If it is lubricated first you will prevent dirt, fertiliser and water from entering the bearings. After cleaning, grease and oil all items once again for conservation."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The advantages of this method of working are:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 additional checks on the machine right after work,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 ensuring the longevity of the machine,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 less delays due to problems while working with the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "TIP When using a high-pressure cleaner, do not aim it at the seals and the breathers. That way you will prevent dirt and moisture from entering the gearboxes."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Furthermore, do not set up electrical components. Water can cause electrical failures."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See \u00bbBe careful while cleaning with high pressure cleaners\u00ab on page 117,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Clean the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Let the machine dry."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Paint any damaged paintwork."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lubricate and oil all points once again to ensure conservation."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbMaintenance intervals\u00ab on page 125."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Provide white parts such as piston rods of hydraulic cylinders with preservative grease or inject the (white) metal parts of the machine with preserving liquid (supplied) for protection against corrosion."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only use grease that would not harden or dry. That will prevent damage to cylinder oil seals."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "121"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 122,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "122"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Repair damage safely and without delay"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Repair the machine safely before you continue with work:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 place the tractor and machine on a firm, straight surface,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the PTO shaft,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 disconnect the tractor if possible,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait until all parts have stopped moving. The mass (inertia) could keep the machine running for a bit!"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 place wheel chocks in front of the wheels of a machine with parking wheels to prevent it from rolling away,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 use the correct tools,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 bigger or heavier parts must be locked and secured to lifting gear when being replaced,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 parts that could move unintentionally must be supported and secured,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 do not climb on parts of the machine that are not in use. Only use stepladders, ladders or other tools intended for this purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 disconnect the feed while working on the electric system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 disconnect the cables from the battery and the dynamo before arc welding on the tractor or the connected machine!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Performed by an authorised person"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Always have an authorised expert perform maintenance and repairs as prescribed in, as prescribed in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbAuthorisation\u00ab on page 11."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "All forms of responsibility of the manufacturer become null and void and the guarantee lapses if maintenance and repair work are performed by an unauthorised person."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 123,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not modify the machine"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Do not modify the machine in any way. Unauthorised modifications may impair the function and/or safety and affect the life of the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Only use original parts when replacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Using other non-genuine parts could lead to problems and unsafe situations when using the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Accessories and parts must be correctly mounted"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Assemble accessories and parts according to specifications and attach them only for their designated purpose; ensure that it is locked correctly. Accessories and parts which are not fastened securely could lead to personal injury and damage to the crop and machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Tighten all bolts and nuts"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check that all the nuts and bolts are well set. Check this again after one hour of use"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after delivery and"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after maintenance or repairs have been carried out."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid jamming under the sieves"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "There is a risk that parts of your body may get jammed in the hopper during maintenance activities or when closing the sieves. Secure the sieve in an open position and unlock the sieves on the outside. Jamming could cause injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with materials"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You should only come into contact with the materials when cleaning the machine. Always wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves, shoes and goggles. Read and adhere to the additional safety instructions and the of the material producer. Contact with the materials could lead to injury. Contact your physician in such an event!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Explosion danger because of nitrate"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fertiliser that contains nitrate can create an explosion danger if it should come into contact with fire. All fertiliser remnants should therefore be removed from voids, corners, tubes and tubing before welding, cutting or grinding on the machine. An explosion will cause damage to the machine and could lead to personal injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Adhere to all the safety precautions as described in \uf0ae paragraph \u00bbSafety requirements\u00ab from page 10."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "123"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 124,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Oil and grease content"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Never use more oil or grease than prescribed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "A too high oil level may result in an overheated machine and damaged seals."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Waste storage and disposal"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Waste from performing maintenance on the machine could be contaminated with fertiliser, oil and grease. Collect the waste and dispose of it in terms of national regulations."
    },
    {
      "type": "TableItem",
      "table_data": {
        "Part / action": {
          "0": "Central gearbox gearboxes of the spreading discs",
          "1": "Lubricate with grease Lubricate with oil"
        },
        "Quantity": {
          "0": "2 x 0.25 litre 1.5 litres",
          "1": "1 to 2 times"
        },
        "Specifications": {
          "0": "EP00/000 gear grease EP00/000 gear grease",
          "1": "Shell Rodina 2, Castrol GS2 or equivalent MIL-L-2105C, SAE 80W-90"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "124"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 126,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Lubricating points"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Coupling shaft with quick lock"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Discharge bushings"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Actuators"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Grease nipples"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Grease nipples"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "126"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "All lubricating nipples of the machine can be filled with a universal grease type."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See \u00bbOil and grease content\u00ab on page 124."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See \u00bbMaintenance intervals\u00ab on page 125."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The coupling shaft is provided with grease nipples."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lubricate the nipples."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the condition of the protection sleeves and the check chains."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Replace them if damaged."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The discharge bushings are attached lower down to the agitator axle and have 2 grease nipples."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the discharge bushings"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See the software instruction manual."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the spreading disc by hand until both grease nipples are visible."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Grease the 2 nipples of both discharge bushings."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The actuators are provided with 1 grease nipple."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Grease the nipple of all four actuators."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 127,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Applying or adding grease"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Coupling shaft profiled tubes You must grease the profiled tubes of the coupling shaft regularly. Ap-"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Central gear box"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "gearboxes of the spreading discs"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "There is grease in the gearbox below the spreading discs. The level of the grease under the filler opening must be 35 mm when the machine has been standing still for a short time."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove dirt, fertiliser or grease from the gearbox."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the gearbox by removing the cap from the filler opening."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Measure the level of the grease."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Add grease until the desired level is reached."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the filler opening."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "ply grease to the contact surfaces of both of the profiled tubes should you note during coupling or decoupling that the halves of the coupling shaft are not sliding in and out smoothly. This should at any rate be done at least once per season."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Detach the coupling shaft on the one side."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Pull the shaft halves away from each another."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Grease the running surface of the inner profiled tube."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Slide the coupling shaft halves into each other."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the coupling shaft."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Hook the check chains to the tractor side."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The central gearbox consists of 2 compartments filled with gear wheel grease EP 00/000. The grease in principle never needs to be replaced."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Each compartment holds 0.25 litre."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the level regularly."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove dirt, fertiliser or grease from the gearbox."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the cap from the dipstick and filler opening."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fill the gear box with new grease until it almost comes out of the opening."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Replace the cap."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "127"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 128,
