{
  "page_number": 131,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking the hydraulic system"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Replacement intervals"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Hydraulic oil is under high pressure"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Never try to stop a leak with your fingers. Never try to locate a hydraulic leak or try to contain it by hand! When inspecting always use appropriate aid (e.g. a piece of wood or sheet metal) and wear safety goggles, safety gloves and gloves! High pressure fluid easily penetrates skin and clothes, causing severe injuries. In the event of injury, contact your physician immediately!"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Do not exceed the maximum hydraulic pressure of 210 bars"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Prevent the pressure in the hydraulic system from exceeding 210 bars! Working above the permitted pressure may damage your machine and result in dangerous situations."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Keep your distance from the hydraulics during inspecting and test running"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Use a stick to bend the hydraulic hoses when checking them for leakage. That way you will keep at sufficient distance. Oil jets or hoses that snap back may cause serious physical injury due to the prevailing pressure and temperature."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Work safely on the hydraulic system"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The hydraulic system could be under high pressure. Do not work on the hydraulic system without:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 releasing the pressure from the hydraulic system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching the tractor off,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the key must be removed from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 using the proper tools,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear safety glasses, gloves and shoes."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Working in an unsafe manner on the hydraulic system could lead to injury and damage to the machine. In the event of injury, contact your physician immediately! There is also the risk of infection!"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Before operating the hydraulic system, check all connections and hoses for damage and leakage."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Regularly inspect the hydraulic system (hoses, pipes, connections). All hoses, piping and connecting points must be checked regularly, but at least once a year, by an expert for leakages or visible damage! The lifetime of a hose should be 6 years maximum (see the production date on the hoses)."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Damaged or old parts must be replaced with new ones that comply with the technical specifications of the manufacturer of the machine. Damage to the hydraulic system could lead to injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "131"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 132,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Inspection criteria"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Replacing instructions"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "132"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is not permitted to carry out repairs on hydraulic hoses! Replace hoses if the following is detected during inspection:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 damage to the exterior up to the armouring (such as abrasion marks, cuts and tears),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 the exterior becoming brittle (tears in the hose),"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 distortion not normal for the pattern of the hose while under pressure, as well as without pressure or with bends, e.g. layers pealing off and blisters forming,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 leakages,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 not mounted as per requirements,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 damage or distortion of the hose block, which would compromise the strength of the block or the connection between the hose and the regulating block,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 hose coming out of the connectors,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 corrosion of the connector which would compromise the function and strength,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 exceeding the storage and the operating limits."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Only use original parts when replacing hoses. Hoses must be placed and mounted in the proper way. Be careful not to change the connections. Replaced hoses must be suitable to the permitted work pressure and be resistant to chemical, mechanical and thermal loads. Only use hose clamps made from stainless steel."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Run the hydraulic control valves until all the cylinders are engaged."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on the ground or on firm supports on a firm, level ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Take the pressure off the hydraulic system."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system and the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Disengage the machine."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbDisconnecting the machine\u00ab on page 119."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Demount the connectors with the proper tools."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Collect the oil that drips from the cylinders and the hoses."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Mount new hoses and put them so that they would not get pinched."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Dispose of the collected oil as required by national legislation."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Operate the hydraulic control valves of the tractor very carefully at first after replacing the hoses as there could still be pockets of air in the pipes! Open and close all the hydraulic control valves a few times before you start working."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 133,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking and setting the dosing mechanism"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and safety gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while adjusting and checking the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Work safely while checking and adjusting:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you start with the adjustments,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Check the settings of the dosing mechanism:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after the first 10 running hours,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 for each season,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 after every 100 operational hours,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 if the spreading pattern between the left and right spreading discs differs more than 3%."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbTest the left and right spreading patterns\u00ab on page 78."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "133"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 134,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Set the position of the dosing mechanism"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The dosing mechanism must be mounted exactly in the middle above the spreading discs. The agitator axle must turn freely from the seal ring."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "agitator axle"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "agitator axle"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Seal ring"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Seal ring"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Dashboard"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Dashboard"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "fastening bolt"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "fastening bolt"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "134"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If you open the filters, you should block them to prevent unwanted closing."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on the ground or on firm supports on a firm, level ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system and the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the sieves with the included attachment and deposit it."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the agitator from the agitator axle."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if the distance between the agitator axle and the seal ring is the same on all sides."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the distance is not equal all over the position of the dosing plate can be changed with regards to the agitator axle."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the dashboard by loosening the 3 fixing knobs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the nuts on the 4 fastening bolts with which the dosing mechanism is attached to the hopper a few times to loosen them."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Move the dosing plate so that the distance between the agitator axle and the seal ring is the same on all sides."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Fasten the nuts on the 4 fastening bolts again without moving the dosing plates again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Put the agitator back on."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Reattach the dashboard with the three fixing knobs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the connections as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbChecking and setting the discharge point setting mechanism\u00ab on page 136."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 135,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Setting the dosing baffles"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Fixing slot"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is necessary to set the dosing plates to the correct positions to each other to ensure correct dosing. If the dosing openings do not close well you will loose unnecessary fertiliser and the application rate will be higher than intended with a specific dosing setting. If the baffles slide far over each other the application rate will be much lower than expected."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the dosing plates are mounted in the correct positions, you will see a small crack of light when the dosing openings are closed."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Close the spreader dosing units on the control box. The actuators must be closed properly."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on the ground or on firm supports on a firm, level ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system and the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Open the sieves with the included attachment and deposit it."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if you can see a small crack between the dosing baffles."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 If not, move the actuator attachment point on the dosing mechanism until a small chink is visible between the dosing plates."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Start the tractor and open and close the dosing units by operating the start and stop keys a few times."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system and the tractor off and remove the keys from the ignition."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check if you can see a small crack between the dosing baffles."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "135"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 136,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking and setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "setting mechanism"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "the discharge point"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Fixing knobs"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "136"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and safety gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while adjusting and checking the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Work safely while checking and adjusting:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you start with the adjustments,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the form of the spreading pattern is not the same on the left and on the right and the difference in the application rate is more than 3% it could be caused by a difference in position of the discharge point with regards to the spreading disc between the left and right sides. The distance between the inside of the rope and the opening of the discharge bushing must be 109 mm ."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place the machine on the ground or on firm supports on a firm, level ground."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the first checks as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbChecking and setting the dosing mechanism\u00ab on page 133."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the electronic control system and the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Specify the discharge position Q on the terminal."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Press successively start and stop spreading to activate the correct position."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 137,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the rope as per the illustration."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Measure the distance between the inside of the rope and the opening of the discharge bushing carefully."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the measured distance is more or less than 109 mm, do the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Loosen the 2 bolts of the actuator plate slightly."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Slide the actuator plate until the distance between the inside of the rope and the opening of the discharge bushing is 109 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Re-fasten the 2 bolts without sliding the actuator plate again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the check on the other side as well."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Secure the dashboard by fastening the 3 fixing knobs."
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "137"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 138,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
