    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Checking and setting the discharge bushing height"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Spreading disc"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Spreading disc"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Fixing knobs"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Dashboard"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "Fixing knobsDashboard"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "138"
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Avoid contact with the fertiliser and other material"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You will most likely get into contact with the fertiliser and other material you may wish to spread while filling, adjusting and testing the spreader. Wear protective clothing and safety gloves, read the safety instructions provided by the supplier and follow their directions. Contact with these materials could cause physical harm."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Be careful that nothing gets jammed"
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "It is easy for parts to get jammed while adjusting and checking the spreader."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Work safely while checking and adjusting:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switching off the electronic control system,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 switch the tractor off and remove the key from the ignition,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 engage the parking brake of the tractor,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wait for all machine parts to come to a standstill before you start with the adjustments,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 wear protective clothing, such as safety gloves and shoes,"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\u00b7 carefully follow the instructions given."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Friction with these materials could cause physical injury."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The distance between the discharge bushing and the spreading disc must be 1.0 mm ."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the distance is too great, the fertiliser does not flow through the discharge point opening onto the spreading disc but onto a random point below the discharge bushing. This results in a disrupted spreading pattern."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the distance is too short, a full hopper may rest partly on the spreading disc, which seriously damages the machine as a result."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Attach the empty machine and raise it to working height (75 cm)."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Place heavy, stable supports under the ends of the lifting arms."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the arms onto the supports. Now the machine cannot drop accidentally."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Switch the tractor off, remove the key from the ignition and engage the parking brake of the tractor."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Measure the distance between the spreading disc and the discharge bushing."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can use a feeler gauge to measure short distances accurately."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "If the measured distance is more or less than 1.0 mm, do the following:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Remove the dashboard by loosening the 3 fixing knobs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the lock nuts on the 4 fastening bolts with which the dosing mechanism is attached to the hopper a few times to loosen them."
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 139,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": "INDICATION"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Bayonet ring"
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "PictureItem",
      "caption": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn the nuts on the 4 fastening bolts so that the dosing mechanism moves upward."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "The dosing mechanism is now higher than the spreading disc and discharge bushing. Turn the dosing mechanism upwards until you have good access to the bolts attaching the discharge bushing to the agitator axle star."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Unscrew the bolts attaching the discharge bush to the star a few times."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Move the discharge bushing upwards or downwards until the distance to the spreading disc is 1.0 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "You can also put 1.0 mm thick plates between the discharge bush and the spreading disc and lower the discharge bush onto them."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn on the bolts attaching the discharge bushing to the agitator axle star."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the height again and adjust it if necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Lower the dosing mechanism by turning the fastening bolt nuts upward."
    },
    {
      "type": "SectionHeaderItem",
      "text": "Lower the dosing mechanism until the bayonet ring has moved halfway across the bolts attaching the discharge bushing to the star."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check the position of the dosing mechanism relative to the agitator axle. The distance between the agitator axle and the sealing ring must be the same on all sides."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae See paragraph \u00bbChecking and setting the dosing mechanism\u00ab on page 133."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Turn on the lock nuts on 4 fastening bolts without moving the dosing mechanism again."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Check that the agitator is not in contact with the bolts attaching the agitator seal ring."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Reattach the dashboard with the three fixing knobs."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Perform the check on the other side as well."
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf034 Finally, check the position of the dosing mechanism and the position of the dosing baffle as described in"
    },
    {
      "type": "ListItem",
      "text": "\uf0ae paragraph \u00bbChecking and setting the dosing mechanism\u00ab on page 133."
    },
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "139"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "page_number": 140,
  "items": [
    {
      "type": "TextItem",
      "text": "Maintenance"
    },
